title: italian vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Marinate at least 24 hours.
Excellent for large group dinners.

title: baked sweet potatoes and apples
directions: If using fresh yams, peel and slice to 1/8-inch thickness.

title: strumpfander(garters)
directions: Roll out dough into a thin sheet.
Cut with jaggling iron into 1 x 5-inch strips.
Tie each strip once, like a loose knot, leaving small hole in middle of knot.
Fry in hot fat (they should rise almost instantly to the surface).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
They are better on second day than on first.
This comes from a very old
Moravian cookbook from my hometown in Indiana.

title: choco-chip meringue bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix by hand until well combined.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch or	a
x
10-inch
pan.
Prepare frosting mix as directed
on package;
spread frosting on unbaked fudge base. Keep
frosting about
2-inches from pan edge.
(Frosting will spread
while baking.)
Sprinkle	pecans	and chocolate chips over frosting. Bake
at
for
20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick
inserted near
edge
comes out clean. (Choco-chips will not melt.) Yield: 3 dozen bars.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In large saucepan, bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to boil.
Add oatmeal, pecans or coconut and vanilla in boiling mixture.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Cookies are ready to eat shortly.

title: southern fried potatoes
directions: Saut onion in Crisco oil in heavy 10-inch cast-iron skillet until transparent.	Add potatoes.
Fry potatoes until they are tender and golden, turning as necessary.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peas oriental
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except onion rings and place in buttered casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cover with the onion rings and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Combine thawed Cool Whip topping with strawberry yogurt. Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 5 cups.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown hamburger in frying pan on stove top.
Drain grease. Add ketchup (enough to add red color to beef).
Put in shallow glass baking dish.
Cut sharp cheese into slices.
Arrange over top of hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for a few minutes until cheese melts.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Thoroughly beat in egg and vanilla extract, then blend in dry ingredients.
Mix in chopped Baby Ruth.
Drop by half teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at
375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: mom's picante sauce
directions: Place vegetables in processor one at a time to chop.
Place in large saucepan and add seasonings.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Pour into pint jars and seal; process in boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: crockpot turkey
directions: Coat inside of a 4-qt. crockpot with cooking spray.
Add stuffing mix, onion, celery and cranberries.
Combine broth and melted butter.
Pour over stuffing and stir gently.
Remove string from turkey breast and rinse.
Place turkey on top of stuffing. Combine salt, pepper and thyme.
Sprinkle over turkey.
Cover and cook on HIGH for 1 hour.
Reduce to LOW and cook 5 to 6 hours until a meat thermometer inserted in turkey registers 170 degrees. Remove turkey to a serving platter.
Stir stuffing gently, cover and let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Prepare gravy.
Spoon stuffing around turkey on platter.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: easy delicious chili
directions: Saute garlic in 2 tablespoons Crisco; add meat.
Saute until brown.
Add chili bowl; mix well.
Cook, covered, on low fire until tender.
Add 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix well.
Add water and hot sauce.
Continue to cook 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with beans or rice.

title: pork chop noodle casserole
directions: Place
the
cooked noodles in a small individual casserole. Add
grated
onion,
salt
and
pepper, and sage to the tomato juice.
Pour the tomato juice mixture over the noodles. Place
the browned pork chop on the noodles.
Cover the casserole and bake in a moderate oven for about 1/2 hour.
Exchanges:
2 meat or 3 ounces cooked meat, 1 vegetable, 1 bread, 287 calories.

title: jerica's french toast
directions: Beat egg, cinnamon and sugar in medium to small mixing bowl. Dip 1 slice of bread into bowl.
Put 1 teaspoon butter into heated pan along with 1 slice of bread.
Fry until lightly browned. Repeat the process for the second slice.
Serves 2 people.

title: dill dip (for fresh vegetables)
directions: mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with all your favorite fresh vegetables.

title: pork-spinach pie
directions: Place frozen pie shell on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 325°.
Sprinkle cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook sausage until brown; drain off fat.
Stir in stuffing mix and spinach; spoon over cheese.
Combine beaten eggs and light cream.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake uncovered in a 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: doris brittian's squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dieter's cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and soda in a medium bowl.
Stir well.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour batter into a 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until cornbread is golden.
Yields 9 servings.

title: lo-cal topping(use instead of whipped cream)
directions: In bowl, place water, lemon juice and vanilla.
Sprinkle dry milk on top.
With electric mixer, beat until stiff (about 10 minutes).
Beat in sugar.
Continue beating until stiff enough to hold soft peaks (about 5 minutes) more.
Use instead of whipped cream to top desserts.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or 20 servings (2 tablespoons each).

title: skillet chicken with orange and vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken; cook and stir until golden, about 3 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
To skillet, add mushrooms, carrots and onion.
Cook and stir until onion is transparent, about 5 minutes.
In measuring cup, mix broth, cornstarch, ginger, salt, garlic powder; stir into skillet.
Add broccoli; cover and simmer until broccoli is crisp-tender, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and heat.
Top with orange sections; may be served over steamed rice.
Yields 4 portions/7 cups (per portion:
253 calories, 49 mg. cholesterol).

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and butter in a large mixing bowl.
Add salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir thoroughly. Pour into greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with crushed cornflakes mixed with melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crescents and let cool.
Spread on softened cream cheese mixed with sour cream or creamy Italian dressing to spreadable consistency.
Cover with vegetables.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cover and chill until served.

title: crescent squares
directions: Lay out 1 package of rolls on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Place mixture on top of rolls.
Place second package of rolls on top of mixture.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Let cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: greek macaroni
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion. Stir tomato paste, salt and cinnamon into meat. Set aside.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tortillas, in a large bowl. Fill tortillas.
Roll up and place in greased baking dish.
Pour over remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick of margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 20 minutes.
Spread over crumb mixture.
For the next layer, spread the pineapple and bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over all. Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts and decorate top with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in the butter.
Combine all ingredients and grate cheese on top (medium Cheddar).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: basic vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1 gallon hand turn or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Ripen ice cream 1 hour, if desired.

title: joy's family cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a large saucepan (3-quart size; heavy pot).
Add milk and gradually mix thoroughly.
Bring to a bubbly boil on high heat, stirring continuously.

Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil the mixture without stirring until it reaches a temperature of 232° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water (10 to 15 minutes). Remove saucepan from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir! Allow fudge to cool at room temperature until it reaches 110° (about 15 minutes).
Beat by hand until the fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly pour and spread fudge in a lightly buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan (or cookie sheet for smaller pieces).
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen squares.

title: chili
directions: Brown the hamburger; add to tomatoes, sauce, beans and seasonings.
Simmer until heated thoroughly.
Serve or refrigerate.
The flavor improves if you wait a day or two to eat it.

title: poppy seed french bread
directions: Combine butter, cheese and poppy seeds.
Spread on both sides of each piece of bread.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 16 minutes, turning once.

title: dairy queen blizzard
directions: Freeze the Heath bar.
Break the candy into tiny pieces with a knife handle before removing from wrapper.
Combine all of the ingredients in the blender and blend for 30 seconds on medium speed.
Stop the blender to stir the mixture with a spoon; repeat until well mixed.
Pour into a 16 ounce glass.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except the sliced egg and paprika) in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Arrange the sliced, hard-cooked egg over top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill before serving.
Yields 8.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Pour water into shallow bowl and sprinkle yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar over it.
Let stand 2 or 3 minutes; stir well.
Sit in unlighted oven for 5 minutes or until doubled.
Combine 3 cups of flour, then remaining 1/2 cup of sugar and the salt in a deep mixing bowl and make a well in the center.
Add the yeast mixture, egg yolks and milk with a large spoon.
Slowly mix together, then stir until smooth.
Place all of dough on floured board and knead, sprinkling flour over if necessary to make firm dough.
Knead 10 minutes.
Spread the tablespoon of butter inside a deep mixing bowl.
Place dough in bowl; turn over.
Drape with towel; let rise 1 hour or until doubled.

title: browned rice pilaf
directions: Coat a medium saucepan with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add rice and garlic; saute 3 minutes or until rice is lightly browned, stirring often.
Add oregano and next three ingredients; stir well.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add carrots and red pepper; toss gently.
Cover and cook an additional 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: roast beef supreme
directions: Sprinkle dry onion gravy mix on bottom of pan.
Set meat on top of dry mix.
Pour half of mushroom soup over roast.
Place peeled carrots and potatoes (halved) on top of roast.
Pour rest of mushroom soup over potatoes and carrots.
Cook at 300° for 4 hours.

title: electric skillet dinner
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Shape into two small loaves. Brown on both sides in electric skillet.
Pour tomato soup over loaves.
Simmer for about 40 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes (more soup, if needed) and simmer until done.
Very tasty meal!

title: steak "stuff"
directions: Meat:
Season chip steak well with meat tenderizer, soul seasoning or seasoned salt, onion powder or flakes and pepper.
For more tender steak, beat meat.
Cut steak into small strips or squares.

title: zucchini crabcakes
directions: Mix
zucchini,	egg
and butter;
add bread crumbs, Old Bay, mustard and onion.	Roll in bread crumbs.
Don't make the cakes too large.	Chill.	Fry in oil until brown.

title: extra tender pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into oiled skillet or waffle iron.

title: hawaiian pork
directions: Beat egg thoroughly in medium bowl. Add water, flour and salt; beat until smooth. Stir in meat, mixing until coated. Melt shortening in medium skillet. Add meat mixture; cook and stir until meat is brown. Remove from heat; keep warm.

title: mexinut dip(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe container.
Cover. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes. Stir.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Stir before serving. Serve with crackers, corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients, except catsup, in saucepan and cook slowly about 30 minutes.
This is an excellent mopping sauce for any kind of meat.
Adjust the vinegar and sugar, if desired, for extra sweetness and tartness.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper, celery, sausage and ground chuck until tender.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour on top of roast and bake at 350° for 4 hours until meat falls apart.
Remove bones and skin and place back in oven until sauce is almost absorbed.

title: caraway rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in small bowl.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups stock, molasses, oil and salt. Stir in rye flour and beat until smooth.
Add yeast mixture, caraway seed, powdered milk and soy grits.
Stir in enough whole wheat flour to make soft for kneading.
Let rest 10 minutes.

title: orange blossom creams
directions: Beat egg whites and cream together, then add vanilla and salt. Add 1/4 of sugar at a time and repeat until all is used.
Last, blend in the butter and knead the mixture until it is firm and dry.
Place in a covered bowl and set aside for several hours. Shape into 35 pieces the size of a hickory nut; press a piece of orange peel into center of each piece, leaving part of the peel exposed.
Roll each in moist coconut.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of the mushroom soup, beef onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
In 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Spoon off 2 tablespoons dripping; reserve.

title: lentil soup(low cholesterol)
directions: Place all ingredients into a 6-quart pan half filled with water; simmer for 2 hours.
Can add rice when serving.

title: chocolate-banana cream pie
directions: In crust in single layer, arrange the 2 sliced bananas.
Spoon glaze over the bananas.
Spread to cover.

title: orange coconut crescent rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup fluted tube pan (nonstick too) with solid shortening.
Combine sugar, coconut and orange peel.
Remove crescent dough from can in rolled sections; do not unroll.
Cut each section into 4 slices.
Dip both sides of each slice in butter, then in coconut mixture.
Stand slices on edge, slightly overlapping.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over slices.
Drizzle remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 32 minutes.
Cool in pan 1 minute.
Turn on plate.

title: frosted creams
directions: Mix all ingredients; place batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with thin powdered sugar frosting.

title: greek sarmas(stuffed grape leaves)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients with 1/2 cup tomato sauce in bowl. Place mixture in a grape leaf and fold around mixture.
Place each grape leaf roll in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top and pour water to cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quick coconut pie(no crust)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in electric blender; blend on low speed 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into 2 lightly greased 8-inch pie plates and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over egg mixture.
Press coconut into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Chill before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes before mixing the first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Put 1/4 cup margarine and crushed corn flakes over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: festive pork roast
directions: Cut a slit lengthwise through center of pork (not all the way through).
Lay flat.
Rub with garlic, salt and pepper to taste; sprinkle with raisins.
Close roast and tie with a string.
Place rosemary on top.
Wrap roast with heavy-duty foil.
Poke several small holes through foil into pork on all sides.
Place in roasting pan.
Roast in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheesy chicken crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place about 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of each triangle.
Roll triangle up, starting at shortest side; roll to opposite point.
In medium saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour soup mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon over rolls.
Arrange the filled crescent rolls in the hot soup mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown, at 375°.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, chop up beef.
Cut the stalk of green onions.
Mix all together.
Crush up Townhouse crackers.
Roll mixture in the crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: empanaditas
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; set aside.

title: sneaky petes
directions: Mix and freeze in plastic container.
Put in punch bowl just before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together with hand and form into small balls.
Chill in refrigerator approximately 1 hour.
Put toothpicks into balls. Mix chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler until melted.
Dip balls into mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: apple-oatmeal crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples and put in buttered baking dish.
Melt butter and mix other ingredients all together.
Spread over apples and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until apples are done.
Great topped with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream!

title: bran muffins by the pailful
directions: Combine brans and salt; stir in boiling water then buttermilk. Cool to lukewarm.
Cream together in mixing bowl the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir into bran mixture.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to bran mixture and stir just enough to dampen dry ingredients. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
(It will keep 4 weeks.)

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together into a bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening and peanut butter.
Blend with a pastry blender or two knifes until mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Combine and add milk and eggs.
Mix just until blended. Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Heat a large pan of water to boiling.
Put cabbage heads in water only to wilt.
Mix ground chuck with rice, salt and pepper. Make small meat balls from meat mixture.
Remove cabbage from water.
Take cabbage leaves and wrap a meat ball in it.
Repeat until all meat balls are used.

title: linguine al pesto
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a food processor at medium speed for 3 to 4 minutes.
Set aside.

title: tortilla pizzas
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet over medium heat.
Drain. Stir oregano and salt into beef.
Lightly brush tortillas with oil.
Bake on two large baking sheets at 400° for 3 minutes. Spoon beef mixture evenly over tortillas. Top with equal amounts of tomato.
Sprinkle with basil and cheeses.
Return to oven and bake 12 to 14 minutes or until tortillas are lightly browned. Serves 4.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice.
Mix sour cream, taco mix and mayonnaise.
Spread beans on large platter; top with avocado mixture and layer with sour cream mixture, tomatoes, olives and sprinkle with onions.
Top with cheese.

title: potato soup
directions: Put chicken broth, celery, carrots, onions, potatoes and thyme in pot with just enough water to cover.
When tender, add milk and white corn.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Put through masher.
If needs thickening, add small amount of flour.
Takes about 1 hour.

title: caramel pie
directions: In a large skillet, let melt and brown the 1 1/2 cups white sugar.
Add hot water; simmer until dissolved.
Add custard mixture of:
egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, whole egg, milk and vanilla. Cook until thick.
Pour into baked crust; top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: broiled lemon chicken
directions: Lightly flatten chicken breasts to uniform thickness.
For marinade, in small bowl, combine Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, garlic, pepper and lemon peel.
Place chicken in shallow dish. Pour marinade over chicken.
Cover.
Chill 30 minutes, turning once.
Place chicken on broiler pan; brush with oil.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat source 3 to 4 minutes; turn.
Brush with marinade, then with oil.
Broil an additional 3 to 4 minutes or until cooked. Serves 4.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar, syrup, water, egg whites and salt.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, beating with electric mixer or rotary beater until mixture stands in peaks. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and continue beating until frosting holds deep swirls.
Recipe is for 2 layers, make extra for 3.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits.
Add margarine, cheese, seasoned salt and pepper while grits are hot.
Cool, then beat in eggs.
Bake at 350° in flat dish, 2-inches deep, until golden brown.

title: kopytka from potatoes(servings:  6)
directions: Rub warm, cooked potatoes through a sieve or put through a meat grinder.
Cool the potatoes and beat in egg.
Add flour and salt.
Mix; place on a pastry board dusted with flour and knead to a smooth dough.
Divide the dough into 3 or 4 parts; form into finger-thick rolls and slice diagonally into small dumplings 1-inch thick.
Cook in a large amount of salted water.
Take out the cooked kopytka with a straining spoon and drain well.
On a dish, pour hot butter or pork fat with cracklings over this.
One small, finely chopped, onion may be fried in the pork fat.
The kopytka may be cooked a day ahead.
Before serving, throw them into boiling salted water and bring to a boil only once.
They will be like fresh.
They also taste exquisitely if reheated by frying.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease glass pie plate, 9 x 1 1/2-inches. Beat milk, sugar, vanilla, eggs and baking mix 15 seconds in blender on high.
Add cream cheese.
Beat on high 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except cabbage leaves.
Form mixture into small balls.
Wrap cabbage leaves around balls. Secure with toothpick.
Place rolls in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water; place top on Dutch oven and cook slowly for about 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together until mixture feels soft and sticks together.
Add a little warm water, if necessary; form into balls.
Fry in olive oil until very dark brown, turning often. This may be added to your favorite tomato sauce or can be served alone.

title: elmer fudpucker cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, using cake mix and pudding mix dry. Beat for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hess's strawberry pie
directions: Make a paste of water and cornstarch.
Add sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until the mixture boils.
Continue to cook over low flame until mixture is clear and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add package of Jell-O.
Cool.
Place berries in pie shell. Pour mixture evenly over berries; chill.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is browned; drain. Stir in water, taco sauce, chilies, 1/4 cup olives and seasoning mix. Cook over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes. Layer half of broken taco shells on bottom of greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Cover with 1/2 of meat sauce. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese. Repeat with remaining shells, meat sauce and cheese. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted. Top with remaining olives and tomatoes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix well and pour into tube pan.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done at 350°.
Pour icing (recipe follows) over hot cake after removing it from the oven.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix cake mix (minus 1 cup), 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Press mixture in bottom of pan.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large pot over medium-high heat.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in corn and remove from heat.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
When cheese melts, add to vegetable mixture, stirring until well blended. Heat through, but do not allow to boil.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix thoroughly; form into small ball.
Press pecans in center. Cook in a 350° oven for 8 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken broth with soup, margarine, salt and pepper.
Heat and pour over chicken.

title: briar patch bake
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce and onion; heat. Prepare dinner as directed, except using 1/2 cup milk.
Layer half of dinner in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture. Top with remaining dinner.
Cover, bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: candied pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients and microwave on Roast (70% power) for 6 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking until crystallized (8 to 10 minutes more).
Stir occasionally.
Spread pecans on waxed paper, separating pecans.
Let set until firm.

title: seafood salsa
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Add wine vinegar, sugar, minced onions, garlic and salt to taste.
Chill and serve with crackers and prawns.
Makes 50 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with potato chips (crushed) or Italian bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt.
Place pork chops in an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Top each chop with an onion and lemon slice, then top with 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and continue cooking, spooning sauce over chops occasionally, until done, about 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and slice thin the apples.
Put them into a large bowl and sprinkle 2 cups sugar over them. Stir often.
Let stand 1 hour.
Beat eggs. Add oil and vanilla.
Pour over the apples.
Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nuts well.
Add to egg and apple mixture. Sprinkle remaining ingredients over the top before baking. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: springtime pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine peas, celery, cauliflower and onions. Combine dressing and sour cream; pour over salad and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Just before serving, stir in bacon and sunflower kernels.

title: macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions.
Drain.
Place in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Set aside.
Place butter in 4 cup glass measure.
Cook on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in flour until blended.
Pour milk into 2 cup glass measure.
Cook on 70 for 2 minutes. Stir into flour-butter mixture.
Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until thickened; stirring frequently.
Add salt and onion.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over macaroni.
Blend well.
Serve immediately.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts, then add oleo.
While warm, add brown sugar.
Pack 1/2 of mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown at 350°.
Cool.
Spread vanilla ice cream over mix.
Cover with other half of mix and freeze overnight.

title: p. b. graham snackers
directions: Combine Crisco, powdered sugar and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until well blended. Stir in 1 cup of crumbs and chocolate chips.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
roll in 1/2 cup of crumbs for a fancier cookie.
Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, pineapple and nuts; blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of a bowl with wafers and alternate with mixture and wafers.
Let mixture be on the top. Chill overnight.

title: joyce's favorite pound cake
directions: Put soft butter in bowl; stir.
Add flavors and salt.
Add sugar; beat until creamy.
Spoon in flour and alternate eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 20 minutes.

title: mesquite grilled pepper chicken
directions: Mix all sauces, including dressing and lemon in saucebowl. Cut ends of peppers off and discard seeds.
Cut peppers lengthwise.
Heat grill and add mesquite chips.
Place chicken on grill, baste chicken with sauce while cooking over a medium to low heat.
Cook and baste 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
While chicken is cooking, saute onions and peppers in small amount of canola oil.
Cook rice.
When chicken is almost finished, sprinkle with cheese, let cheese melt.
Make a bed of rice on individual plates.
Place chicken breasts on each bed of rice, adding peppers and onions on top and sprinkle with fresh, diced Romano tomatoes.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix cucumber, onion, salt and water in large bowl and let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Return vegetables to bowl.	Add sugar, vinegar and dill.
Let stand, stir until sugar dissolves and covers vegetables.	Pack in Ziploc Freezer bags and freeze.
Serve thawed but ice cold.
Yield 1 quart.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: Mix
Jell-O
with
boiling water.
Add fruits and nuts. Pour half
of mixture in mold.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over
top.
Add
remaining mixture and chill until firm. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: christian's chicken pot pie
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, flour bottom of pan and put pie crust in. Poke vent holes in crust bottom with fork. In a large bowl, mix chicken soup, potato soup, 1/2 cup milk, shredded chicken and vegetables. Pour mixture into pie crust. Top with second pie crust and trim edges to fit. Poke vent holes in pie top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray tube pan with Mazola spray. Cut biscuits in quarters. Put plain sugar and cinnamon in bag and shake biscuit pieces (do one can at a time), placing in tube pan after coating with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Melt oleo and brown sugar.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pound cheese cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix together.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: asian haystacks
directions: Melt chips on low.
Stir in nuts and noodles.
Drop onto wax paper and cool.
Freeze (covered) if desired.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Trim off soiled cabbage and remove core.
Put head in boiling water.
Boil for 10 minutes or until leaves are limp (remove from water and separate leaves).
Mix the remainder of ingredients.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion.
Drain and put in crock-pot.
Add soup, enchilada sauce and green chiles.
Cut Velveeta into chunks and add to crock-pot.
Put on high until outside of crock-pot is warm, then turn down to low until cheese melts.
Makes a full crock-pot.
Recipe may be halved.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Grind artichoke hearts in food processor until smooth.
Mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour into dish.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until light brown. Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; add taco mix, 1/2 cup water and taco sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
Cool before adding to salad.
Toss salad ingredients.
Add cool meat mixture, cheese and salad dressing. Stir in taco chips.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook the chicken and cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Make stuffing according to directions.
Add chicken and mayonnaise to stuffing.
Cook the shells and cool.
Stuff the shells with stuffing mixture.
Place in a lasagna pan (all shells will not fit in a 9 x 13-inch pan).
Mix 2 cans of water to the two cans of soup and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can make these ahead of time and refrigerate; just bake a little bit longer.

title: black moons
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely before filling.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle top with extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Mix ingredients together about 2 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.

title: down home bread pudding
directions: Slice
bread
and
toast lightly.
Place in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Beat
eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add hot water to the
egg mixture.
Pour over bread and allow to soak for about
10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cold veggie squares
directions: Without separating dough, roll out both packages onto a baking sheet.
Form a single flat surface.
Bake according to package directions.
Allow to cool.
In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil and garlic powder. Spread mixture evenly over crescent dough surface.
Spread broccoli, cauliflower and carrots over cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle salad seasoning mix over top.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: bev slimm's bread pudding with vanilla sauce
directions: Combine milk and eggs; pour over bread cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch round baking dish.
Place in shallow pan on oven rack; pour hot water around it 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside comes out clean.
Serve with Vanilla Sauce.

title: ricotta squares
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Ricotta and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour mixture over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Open oven door and let cool in oven for 1 hour.
When completely cool, cut into squares and remove from pan with spatula.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Keep refrigerated.

title: san antonio picante sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and mix until well blended, but not pureed totally. Refrigerate for several hours to maximize seasoning.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl; blend thoroughly.
Force dough through cookie press onto chilled baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes, or until set but not browned.

title: butterscotch caramels(takes 3 to 4 hours sometimes, depending on the weather)
directions: Place 1/2 pint cream, syrup and sugar in a heavy pan over low heat; stir constantly.
When mixture comes to a boil, add rest of cream and butter very slowly so that mixture never stops boiling (very important).
Lower heat and cook at a slow boil to a firm ball stage, 246° to 248°.
Sprinkle chopped nuts in a well buttered glass pan.
Add vanilla to mixture and pour over nuts. Cool at room temperature.
Cut into small pieces with sharp scissors and wrap individually in wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.
They taste best served cold.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, pork, eggs, bread crumbs, milk, 1/4 cup of the brown sugar, 2 teaspoons of the mustard and the pepper.
Spread ham mixture in ungreased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Mix remaining brown sugar and mustard; spread over ham mixture.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: meat jamboree
directions: Brown onions and pepper, then add meat and cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and water to meat and cook 5 minutes.
Place 1 cup macaroni in casserole.
Add layer of meat and layer of cheese.
Add second layer of each.
Cover and cook 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with bacon grease, butter, salt, pepper and minced onion until tender.
Drain well.
Mix 1 cup of sour cream and can of cream of chicken with squash.
Put a layer of herb stuffing, a layer of squash and a layer of cheese (9 x 9 pan).
On top, put a layer of herb stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade butter mints
directions: Mix sugar, butter and water.
Color and flavor to taste (approximately 1/8 to 1/4 teaspoon of oil or 1/2 to 1 teaspoon extract).
Shape into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar. Press into candy molds.
Pop out.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: grandma's irish soda bread
directions: Soak raisins in water for 1/2 hour.
Drain.
Mix together soaked raisins and all other ingredients.
Knead and shape into round loaf.
Place in a warm, greased cast-iron pan.
Put a cross on top of bread with a butter knife.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Eat with butter and hot tea!

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine, chunky peanut butter and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Pour melted mixture over Rice Chex.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken and mayonnaise.
Place crumbs in another bowl.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; toss to coat.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tex-mex tortilla soup
directions: Cut chicken into strips; set aside.
In large pot, combine water, beef broth, chicken broth, undrained tomatoes, onion, green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes, add corn, chili powder, cumin, and pepper. Simmer covered for 10 minutes more.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill overnight.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: french dressing(dietetic)
directions: Mix together all ingredients and shake well.
Refrigerate before using.
Note:
May be mixed in blender.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat well.
Dissolve soda in 1 teaspoon of hot water.
Add milk to soda.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites (beaten stiffly but not dry).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours in a tube pan.
Do not open oven door for first hour.

title: peppermint cloud dip
directions: Beat chilled whipping cream and sugar until well mixed.
Add crushed peppermint candy.
Use as a dip with sliced apples.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Gradually add to other mixture. Add vanilla, cinnamon, nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a long pan.

title: cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a Bundt pan, melt 1/4 cup oleo in the oven.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan with the melted oleo.
Cut biscuits into fourths and toss with 1/4 cup melted oleo and dump in Bundt pan.
In saucepan, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute 1 stick oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately invert onto a plate.
Serve warm.
Serves a lot!

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken breasts in shallow baking dish (do not overlap). Sprinkle mushrooms over chicken breasts.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour evenly over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; spoon off excess fat.
Add Ragu sauce and beaten eggs.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Layer half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half cream cheese, half Mozzarella and half Provoli. Top with half of meat sauce.
Repeat process.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(Can be assembled early and refrigerated.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.)
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot sweet pickle relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions, bell peppers and hot peppers.
Add cup of salt, soak overnight.
Rinse in cold water in colander. Mix all other ingredients together. Add to vegetable mixture. Cook 30 minutes.
Seal in jars while hot.

title: quick fudge
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Let come to a boil and boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
In a mixing bowl, put remaining ingredients.
Stir the cooked mixture in the above until well mixed and chips are melted.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; top with a half of pecan.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoon into a bowl of finely chopped pecans; roll until well coated.
Place on waxed paper; chill.
Form fudge in a long roll; roll back and forth to get a round roll.
Roll in waxed paper, chill and slice 1/4-inch thick.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stir with spoon; do not mix with mixer.
Freeze according to your freezer's directions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and onions.
Mix well.
Drop in deep hot grease by spoonfuls and brown on all sides.

title: lobster dip
directions: Boil lobsters 20 to 25 minutes in 1-inch of salted water. Pick out all meat and cut in small pieces.
Set lobster juice aside with meat.
In a small bowl, pour enough warm water to cover over spices; set aside.
In large bowl, mash softened cream cheese; add juice from lobster a little at a time until creamy texture appears.
Add spices and mix together and finally add lobster; mix again.
Form mix into a mound and sprinkle top with chives and parsley.
Spread crackers around dip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Immediately stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in apples, cranberries, oranges and pecans.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with pie filling.
Add condensed milk and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place in glass bowl and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: shrimp-macaroni salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate serve on lettuce.
Garnish with tomato, egg slices, olives or other salad favorites.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut each potato into 6 slices.
Dry the pieces.
Coat with melted butter in baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake covered in single layer for 20 minutes.
Uncover, baste and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: milky way salad
directions: Combine bananas, Cool Whip, candy bars and apples in a bowl. Crush cookies and put on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients and pour 3/4 of batter into tube pan sprayed with Pam.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Put dates, nuts, butter and soda in a bowl.
Heat juice and water until it boils.
Pour over date mixture.
Stir until butter melts.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or 2 small loaves bake for 30 minutes.

title: ginny's cream cheese frosting
directions: In bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla. Beat until light. Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy. Add milk if necessary to make spreadable. Use 1/2 recipe for 9 x 13-inch sheet cake.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until mixture is well blended.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pint.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In glass bowl, combine sugar and syrup.
Microwave 2 1/2 to 3 minutes on High until mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir in peanut butter and cereal.
Shape into balls or drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: 1-2-3-4 layer cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar in bowl.
Alternate flour, eggs and milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 425° until edges of cake are browned lightly, then turn on broiler to brown top.
Make 4 layers and fill with any kind of filling.

title: million dollar cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, then slowly beat in eggs.
Mix in coconut, sugar, flour, cocoa, salt, vanilla and nuts.
This makes a heavy batter.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together; knead several times.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut and place on a cookie sheet or in a baking pan.
Bake at 450° to 500° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beer nuts
directions: Put in a large frying pan. Fry in a frying pan uncovered until water is gone.
Sprinkle salt on a sheet pan; pour nuts on the pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes; turn and stir.
Then bake for 15 minutes more.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown chops in 2 tablespoons oil.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion in butter until soft.
Mix with mushroom soup and milk.
Add tuna.
Mix with cooked noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with potato chips before baking.

title: jerry's strawberry dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Put in bottom of dish.
Combine strawberries and pie gel and spread over cake.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over cake and strawberries. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups and milk.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix stuffing with leftover chicken broth until thin enough to spread.
Spread evenly over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly on top and brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix Crisco with sugar, add eggs, flour (sifted twice), cocoa and salt.
Alternately add buttermilk, then vanilla and food coloring.
Beat well.
Fold in soda dissolved in vinegar.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy bean dip
directions: In blender, puree beans and tomato until smooth. Transfer to a medium saucepan or chafing dish. Add scallions, cheese and chili powder. Cook over low heat, stirring, until cheese is melted and dip is heated through, 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot with crisp tortilla chips for dipping.

title: fabulous crab ball
directions: Cream softened cheese and butter. Add onion, pepper and mayonnaise.
Rinse crab meat. Drain well. Squeeze water from meat. Add to mixture.
Line a small bowl with Saran Wrap.
Pack mixture into bowl. Chill until firm.

title: basic meat stock
directions: Rub the veal or beef bones with oil; place in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Rub the carrots, celery and onion with oil.
Roast everything for 20 minutes, until it is a rich, dark brown.
Remove from the oven.
Place in a pot with the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Skim off foam; simmer 3 to 4 hours to reduce by one-third.
Strain and freeze.

title: jelly
directions: Mix Sure-Jell with juice.
Bring to rolling boil over high heat.
Add sugar and cook for 8 minutes.
Put in jars and seal immediately.

title: aunt catherine's pound cake
directions: Dump into a bowl the sugar, butter (make sure it's at room temperature), milk, eggs, then rest of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not open door until done.

title: arizona schoppert bittingee's chili sauce
directions: Grind all ingredients.
Combine and cook until thick.
Seal in sterilized pint jars.

title: baked rice
directions: Stir together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: walnut stuffing
directions: Melt butter called for in stuffing mix
package directions. Add celery and onion. Cook until tender, but not brown. Add water called for in package directions.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Stir in stuffing mix, parsley flakes and walnuts.
Makes 5 1/2 cups stuffing.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Cook vegetables until fork tender.
Drain.
Combine soup, 1/2 cup of Swiss cheese, pimentos and 2/3 cup of onions.
Mix with vegetables and pour into a baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with rest of cheese and remainder of onions.
Return to oven and bake uncovered for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate fudge divine
directions: Cook slowly, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft-ball stage.
Test by dropping
a few drops in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Cool to lukewarm without stirring. Add flavoring; beat until thick.
Pour in greased dish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts last.
Bake in greased loaf pan in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cheese strips
directions: Mix all filling ingredients well; then spread thinly over bread.
Cut in strips about 1 inch wide and place in freezer on a cookie sheet.
When solidly frozen, store in a plastic freezer bag and remove as needed.
To reheat, bake on a cookie sheet for 10 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.

title: strawberry cottage cheese pie
directions: Cook pineapple,
sugar,
salt
and egg until thickened; add the gelatin.
Let cool.
Beat the chilled evaporated milk, then fold into the chilled mixture and then the cottage cheese and strawberries.
Put it in a baked crust.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding and poppy seed; mix well.
Add other ingredients and beat for 6 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Grease 2 loaf pans; divide batter evenly in the pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat macaroni supper
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter.
Cook onion in butter until tender not brown.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add soup, tomatoes and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add macaroni and green pepper.
Stir and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together eggs and oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Add Bisquick, Parmesan cheese, parsley and oregano.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Add zucchini; mix until moistened.
Sprinkle in salt and pepper as desired. Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce and celery salt.
Toss all other ingredients into mayonnaise mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight so flavors will blend.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Test with toothpick and let cool.
Best to keep overnight before cutting.

title: hawaiian mac-nut brittle
directions: Mix baking soda, vanilla and 1 teaspoon water.
Set aside. Combine water, sugar and corn syrup; heat to 275°.
Add nuts and cook until 302° using candy thermometer.
Remove from heat, add butter and baking soda mixture and stir.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet to cool.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain and put beef in crock-pot. Brown bacon and onion.
Drain.
Add bacon, onions and remaining ingredients into crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low heat for 4 to 6 hours.
Serves a bunch.
If using 2-quart crock-pot, reduce this recipe by half.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter.
Stir into brown sugar until blended.
Cool.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: turkey hawaiian
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and water.
Beat until smooth. Add turkey and stir well until all pieces are coated.
Drop into hot, shallow fat and brown on all sides; keep warm.
Drain pineapple juice into saucepan.
Blend in cornstarch.
Add butter, pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add turkey and serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: light lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle bottom and sides with graham cracker crumbs.
Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into blender container.
Add cottage cheese and cream cheese products; cover.
Blend at medium speed, scraping down sides occasionally, approximately 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth.
Pour into a large bowl.
Stir in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pan or dish.
Chill until set, approximately 4 hours.
When set, ready to serve.
Top cheesecake with pie filling.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add soup, catsup, mustard and a little water if needed.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, soda and oats.
Add egg, oil,
milk, honey, bananas and nuts.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.	Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400°
for
minutes, or until done.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: baba ganoush(from "wings of life" cookbook)
directions: Prick the whole unpeeled eggplant in a few places with a fork, place it on a baking sheet and broil it about 4 inches from the heat in the oven.
Turn it to cook on all sides, until the eggplant is completely collapsed.
This takes about 20 minutes. When the eggplant is cool enough to handle, peel off the charred skin.
Beat the pulp with a fork until it is smooth or puree in blender.
In a separate bowl, mix garlic and salt.
Stir in the tahini.
With a wooden spoon, beat in the lemon juice.
Beat the tahini mixture into the eggplant a little at a time.
The mixture should whip up nicely and turn a lighter color.
Add the fresh parsley and cayenne pepper.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix flour, add salt, cinnamon and soda.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well; bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tossed salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a shaker and shake.
Pour over salad.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Roll into balls.
Dip in sugar and pat down with bottom of glass or mold dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: western bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan; heat through, stirring constantly.
If desired, garnish with snipped parsley. Makes about 2 cups.

title: louise's date nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour alternately with eggs.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Batter will be stiff.

title: acorn squash with dates and walnuts
directions: Cut squash in half crosswise; remove seeds.
Place squash halves, cut side up, in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Combine dates and walnuts; spoon into squash.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine chicken, cheese, celery, onion, mushrooms and sour cream.
Spread out individual biscuits.
Spoon chicken mixture onto center of biscuit and roll up, securing ends so mixture doesn't fall out.
Roll stuffed biscuit in beaten eggs and then in crushed cornflakes.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold.

title: italian wedding cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together; form into a ball with a generous teaspoonful.
Bake at 375°.
Frost while still warm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: lazy day cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice.
While it is standing, brown the ground beef with salt, pepper and onions.
Simmer until onions are tender.
Add tomato soup and heat thoroughly.

title: south-of-the-border pockets
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook for 5 minutes.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes.
Add taco sauce and beans.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes. Spoon chicken mixture into pita pockets.
Top as desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together soup mix and rice in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Place cut up chicken on top.
Add mushroom soup mixed with water. Pour over top.
Bake 2 hours at 325°, no lid.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Form into a ball.
Then roll in nuts.
Chill for 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: kicky korn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Mix corn meal, flour, salt, sugar and baking powder in center. Add beaten eggs, water and grease. Fold in corn, bacon and 1/2 cheese. Pour in greased 9-inch baking dish or pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break and cook spaghetti with 2 chicken bouillon cubes in water. Drain, but do not rinse. Combine all ingredients and put into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 325° covered for 15 minutes and uncovered for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: beef nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix ground beef and all of the other ingredients together in a crock-pot or double boiler and cook until cheese is melted and mixed well.

title: sausage casserole(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Put in casserole dish and cover with foil.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done.
Put grated cheese on top last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: starlight mint cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Blend in eggs, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Enclose a mint wafer in 1 tablespoon of chilled dough. Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix all and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lucia cranberry parfait
directions: In a blender container or food processor bowl, combine 1/2 cup berries and 1 tablespoon of water.
Cover and blend or process until pureed.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg product, sugar and 2 tablespoons water on high speed of electric mixer until mixture is slightly thickened and fluffy (about 8 minutes).
Set aside.
In small bowl, beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold egg mixture into whipped cream.
Fold pureed fruit just until marbled. Pour mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and freeze 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until 1-inch of mixture around the edge is icy, stirring gently after 1 hour.
Stir gently and spoon into dessert dishes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order given.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 60 to 90 minutes.
Check at 60 minutes.
You may want to bake at 325°.
Can be baked in loaf pans.

title: melt queso
directions: Melt together in crock-pot.
Serve over chips.
Makes a bunch.

title: apple-bran streusel muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, cereal, sugar, baking powder, allspice and salt.
In a small bowl, combine egg whites, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until moistened.
Fold in apples.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chuck wagon potatoes
directions: Grease casserole baking dish deep enough to accommodate potato slices and place upright.
Alternate layers of potatoes and onion. Melt oleo and add seasonings except paprika.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Bake at 375° for 40-50 minutes covered.
Uncover and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake an additional 10-15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed using 1/2 cup less milk.
Mix in condensed milk and whipped topping.
Layer wafers, pudding mixture and bananas in a very large covered container.
Keep refrigerated.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Stir together sugar, vinegar and vegetable oil; add all other ingredients, stirring well.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator in a 1/2 gallon container.
Keeps well for a week or more.
Makes 20 servings.

title: yogurt apple salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and oats.
Combine yogurt with a dash of salt.
Add to fruit mixture; toss.
Garnish with celery leaves, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Really delicious.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine, flour and soda.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan, saving some for topping.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon mousse superb
directions: Combine milk, cornstarch, salt and sugar. Cook stirring over medium heat until mixture come to a full boil and thickens. Simmer, stirring for one minute. Break egg yolks into small bowl. Gradually stir in some hot mixture and then put all into saucepan. Cook and stir 1 minute longer. Remove from heat. Blend in lemon peel and juice. Chill until cold to the touch. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into 4 stem dessert dishes. Freeze until firm. Grate on additional peel for garnish.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a large pot and boil until all scum boils out. Drain and wash thoroughly.
Place the ribs into a large pot with 2 to 3 chopped cloves garlic.
Pour soy sauce, white vinegar and brown sugar over ribs with about 1 cup of hot water to avoid burning the ribs.
Lower to low heat and let simmer.
Add oyster sauce; stir occasionally to season in sauce and prevent burning. Add more water if necessary.
Ribs are done when meat falls off bones.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, 1/2 of green chilies, 1 can soup, 1 cup sour cream and spices.
Spoon onto tortillas and fold like a burrito.
Place in baking pan with sides touching each other.
Mix other can of soup, 1 cup sour cream, remaining chilies and milk.
Spread over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over Crispix and mix well.
Pour into big plastic bag and add the powdered sugar.
Shake well.

title: hot pineapple side dish
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Add butter or margarine and 1 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Gently stir in pineapple.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top; drizzle with reserved juice.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs, one at a time, then add blackberries. Mix real good.

title: spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach; set aside.
Saute butter and onion in large saucepan until golden brown.
Turn heat to medium setting. Add cream cheese in small bits, stirring slowly.
Once cream cheese melts, add spinach, artichokes, whipping cream, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Turn into serving dish.

title: brownies
directions: Put in eggs, sugar, melted butter and vanilla.
Beat well, then add rest of ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Pour milk over dry bread crumbs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer at least one hour.

title: cinnamon bread(one and one-half pound loaf for bread machine)
directions: Set machine to dough-mix setting and mix dough, then let dough rest 10 minutes on floured surface.
Flatten to a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll dough, pinch the ends and place in a greased bread pan.
Moisten the top with milk, then sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° until bread is done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all except last two ingredients together.
Put grated Mozzarella cheese in center.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Early in the morning, boil 6 to 8 medium-sized potatoes until just done.
Allow to cool until lukewarm, then peel and slice into a wide bowl (do not pile high).
Top with one very finely chopped medium-size Spanish onion.
Pour just enough boiling water over the onions to moisten the potatoes slightly.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, lemon juice and vinegar (tarragon) according to taste. Mix in 3 to 4 tablespoons Mazola oil.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and taco seasoning.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, add eggs and honey; mix with mixer.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Mix and chill at least 1 hour.
Cut and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Frost.

title: ham delights
directions: Cut rolls completely in half.
(Keep all rolls intact; just slice top off bottom as if making a ham sandwich.) Leave bottoms of rolls in the pan they came in.
Cream the margarine, poppy seed, mustard and chopped onion.
Put 2 layers ham and 1 layer cheese on bottom rolls.
Put tops of rolls back on; spread mixture over tops of rolls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except nuts.
Blend until smooth. Shape in roll, wrap
in
foil and freeze for 2 hours.
Roll in nuts. Keep
chilled
until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cover bone with cold water; bring to a boil.
Skim residue. Lower heat to simmering temperature.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, covered, for approximately 1 hour.
Add chopped vegetables.
Soak barley, changing water 9 times.
Drain and add to soup.
Simmer all ingredients for about 3 to 4 hours or until meat is tender.
Add noodles and spinach leaves.
Cook over low heat another 1/2 hour.
Taste to check on salt and pepper amounts. Serve with French bread.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, salt and water.
Cook until macaroni is tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned on top.

title: squash ring mold
directions: Cook squash as directed on package using only 2 tablespoons water and 2 tablespoons butter.
Beat eggs.
Mix eggs, tomato sauce, onion, salt, pepper and Tabasco and add to squash.
Pour into greased ring mold and place mold in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brisket (crock-pot)
directions: Cook on low overnight.

title: creamy chicken 'n shells salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and chill.
May add additional salad dressing, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: lobster fra diavolo
directions: Put all ingredients (except lobsters and pasta) in a large, nonreactive (not aluminum) pot and bring to a boil.
Add lobsters (or precooked lobster meat) and simmer gently on very low heat for about 1 hour.
Stir often, scraping the bottom of the pot.
Sauce will be thick, light and have a delicate lobster taste.
About 10 minutes before sauce is done, cook the pasta al dente.
Drain quickly.
Put pasta on hot plates.
Pour some sauce over the pasta.
Place split/quartered or lobster meat over the pasta and cover with more sauce.
Enhance taste by sprinkling with grated Romano Pecorino cheese.

title: cereal bars
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Set aside. In a saucepan, bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil. Cook and stir just until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over cereal mixture and toss to coat evenly. Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Cool. Cut into 3 x 3-inch bars.

title: chicken pie supreme
directions: Cook chicken and
debone.
Put	chicken
on bottom of a 2-quart greased
casserole.
Sprinkle
with
pepper. Mix soups and broth until
smooth.
Pour	over
chicken.	Mix
remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over soups. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil; reduce heat.
Gradually beat in two well beaten eggs with whip.
After cools, add salad dressing.
It's ready to enjoy.

title: pimento cheese souffle(marion compton)
directions: Add 1/2 cup hot water to bread in large bowl.
Make paste. Add milk, eggs, pimentos, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour in mix.
Beat well. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°, until brown around edges and light brown on top.
Can be mixed day before.

title: long boy cheeseburgers
directions: Cut one long or 2 short loaves of French bread lengthwise in half.
Mix all the above and spread on the bread.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Add cheese the last 5 minutes to melt.
Cut and serve.

title: crazy cake
directions: Pour cherries into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add pineapple. Spread dry cake mix over all the cherries.
Add nuts.
Cut butter into pieces and spread over the top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Let cool.
Add whipped topping and serve.
Or, serve warm with ice cream.

title: celery slaw
directions: Slice celery in thin diagonal pieces.
Slice onion into thin rings; place in large bowl.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients, except parsley and tomatoes.
Pour over veggies, stir to combine.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Just before serving stir well.
Arrange in bowl.
Garnish with parsley and tomatoes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tandori chicken
directions: In blender, puree onion, garlic, ginger and lemon juice to make a paste.
Add yogurt and all spices; blend to combine.
Add oil and salt and pepper to taste; blend to combine.
Remove skin from chicken.
On breast halves, use a sharp knife to make 2 or 3 (3-inch) slits halfway to the bone.
With the tip of the knife, poke 2 or 3 holes to the bone in the thigh and drumstick of each chicken leg.
Place chicken pieces in a large, nonreactive bowl. Add yogurt mixture; mix to be sure all pieces of chicken are well coated.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator overnight, up to 24 hours. Starting with top side, grill chicken 7 to 8 minutes, allowing pieces to get slightly charred.
Turn and cook 8 minutes longer, or until the juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a knife. If using broiler, procedure and cooking time are about same.
Makes 6 servings.

title: festive whipped cream
directions: Whip cream with confectioners sugar.
Add bourbon or vanilla; beat until stiff peaks form.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Blend these ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Drop cream cheese mixture, by spoonfuls, on top and swirl into chocolate mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cookie monster cookie dough
directions: Pour sugar over butter and blend with fork.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Blend with fork.
Pour flour over mixture.
Add baking powder and salt.
Mix with fork or hand.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll out dough with rolling pin.
Use cookie cutter to shape cookies.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes (until edges are brown).

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix all together until oranges are broken up and batter is smooth.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool!

title: pot roast by pamela
directions: Put onions in Dutch oven.
Cover with 1/2 cup water.
Lay meat on top; add all seasonings (hold flour until later).
Cover and cook on simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Add more water, if needed.
Leave overnight in fridge; skim off fat and slice meat with the grain, removing any fat.
Return to pan.
Blend onions, flour and liquid in blender.
(Remember to discard bay leaves.)
Pour over meat; bring up to a boil for a few minutes.
Then simmer until heated through.

title: double-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat half of the dry cake mix, butter, vanilla and eggs in large bowl on medium speed until smooth or mix with spoon. Stir in remaining cake

mix, nuts and chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are set (centers will be soft). Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes with soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, margarine and seasonings.
Pour into 9 x 14-inch dish.
Combine flakes with margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Soften oleo.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Beat softened oleo until creamy.
Add brown sugar.
Beat well.
Add granulated sugar; beat well.
Add vanilla and eggs again.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture. Then stir in chocolate chips.
Bake on cookie sheet 8 to 12 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes, then remove with metal spatula.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen.
When ready to serve, thaw about 45 minutes and reheat thoroughly.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes; put on plate.
Sprinkle garlic and onion onto slices.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over slice.
Put a teaspoon of oil and a teaspoon of vinegar and spread over slices to moisten crackers.
Cover and chill over 30 minutes.

title: creamy baked rice pudding
directions: *Note:
I add 1 can evaporated milk to the quart of milk.

title: elda's "bride's cocoa cake"
directions: Place dry ingredients in a flour sifter and sift 4 times. Combine eggs, vanilla and sour cream in a bowl and beat together very well.
Add the flour mixture.
Bake at 350°.

title: hash brown breakfast
directions: Spread croutons in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix eggs and milk and pour over croutons. Sprinkle cooked and drained sausage on this. Add shredded cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Pound chicken cutlets until thin.
Roll together chicken cutlet and 1/2 slice of boiled ham.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Flour, salt and pepper the rolled chicken cutlets and brown in oil.

title: chocolate coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cocoa together, then add soda, powder and salt.
Stir in eggs, oil, water, coffee and vanilla.
Stir well with large spoon until all is mixed well.

title: taco dip
directions: This is prepared in layers on the serving platter.

title: paper sack apple pie
directions: Peel and cut apples in chunks.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples and coat well.
Pour in pie shell and sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour, cinnamon and nutmeg with 1 stick butter.
Crumble on top of apples.
Place in large paper bag, roll ends and fasten with paper clips.
Bake for 1 hour on cookie sheet.
This browns beautifully.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together.
Add chopped pecans (optional).
Top with nuts. Use graham cracker crust or plain baked crust.
Set overnight.

title: easy 3-cheese lasagna
directions: Force cheese through sieve.
Rub thoroughly until free from lumps.
Add butter, egg yolks, salt, sugar and flour.
Beat thoroughly until light.
Add well beaten egg whites and fold in carefully.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll with hands into long, narrow roll.
Flatten and cut slantwise into pieces 2 inches long. Cook in salted, boiling water until they rise to the top.
Lift with straining spoon and cover with lightly browned buttered crumbs, if desired.
They are delicious with sour cream flavored with cinnamon and sugar or fresh fruit or preserves.

title: kahlua home brew
directions: Cook and simmer water, sugar and instant coffee for 45 minutes uncovered.
After completely cooled, add 1/5 vodka and vanilla. Store for 3 or 4 weeks before using.

title: kentucky pecan bourbon cake
directions: Break pecan pieces with fingers or chop very coarsely; cut raisins in half and set aside.
Measure the flour after sifting once; then sift twice more.
Take 1/2 cup of this flour and mix with nuts and raisins.
To the rest of the flour, add the baking powder and sift again.
Cream butter and sugar.

Add yolks of eggs one at a time, beating until mixture is smooth and lemon colored. Soak the nutmeg in the whiskey for at least 10 minutes, then add to the butter mixture, alternating with the flour and beating as the batter is being blended.
When it is finished, it looks and tastes a great deal like eggnog.
Slowly fold the raisins and nuts into the batter.
Last of all, fold in the egg whites, stiffly beaten with a few grains of salt.

title: moe's chicken wings
directions: Brown 1/2 the wings at a time for better browning.
Drain oil. Saute garlic.
Add all ingredients plus all wings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes, turning wings once after 10 minutes.
Uncover.
Turn to high and boil wings until glazed, about 10 minutes.

title: quick sauerbraten
directions: Place all ingredients in a glass bowl for about 1 hour.
Turn meat after 30 minutes.
After meat and spices have set for an hour place in a heavy pan and heat for about 45 minutes.
This is a good recipe if meat is a little tough; it will become tender and delicious.
Thicken gravy.
Serve over spatzle or noodles.

title: spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon and reserve grease.
Combine last 5 ingredients in grease.
Stir until all combined.
Pour over shredded spinach, crumbled bacon and mushrooms.

title: bacon 'n cheddar oven pancake
directions: Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch) or use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese evenly into bottom of pan. Beat remaining ingredients with wire whisk or hand beater until well blended.
Pour over bacon and cheese.
Spread batter to edges.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until light golden brown.
