Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: greek oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut each lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Place wedges in a bowl; cover with cold water.
Let stand 30 minutes; drain.

Pat dry with paper towels. Toss potatoes with oil; place, skin side down, on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Combine oregano, pepper and salt; sprinkle evenly over potatoes. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and browned.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with vinegar.
Yields 4 servings.
Serve immediately.

title: special creamed corn
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add cream, milk, sugar, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil; boil and stir for two minutes. Add corn; heat through. Transfer to an ungreased 1 1/2-quart broiler-proof dish. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese. Broil 5 inches from the heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: gwen bradford's ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer, cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and gradually stir in flour mixture until combined well. Stir in coconut, oats and cornflakes.
Drop rounded teaspoons of dough about 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake cookies in batches in middle of oven until browned lightly, 10 to 12 minutes.
Transfer to racks to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put sliced cucumbers in jugs.
Boil 1 gallon of water and salt; pour over cucumbers.
Let set for 1 week.
Pour off water. Add 1 gallon of boiling water and alum powder.
Pour over cucumbers; let set 24 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Add 1 gallon of plain boiling water to cucumbers.
Let set overnight.
Add together the sugar, vinegar and pickling spice; boil together. Pour over cucumbers in jug.
Let set for 3 days.
Drain and save vinegar.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Heat vinegar and pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: uncle deiter's cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; shred potatoes with skins on.
Melt cheese and butter in microwave and fold into the potatoes.
Mix sour cream with ingredients and bake at 325° until top is brown.
This freezes well for further use.

title: pumpkin whip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat pudding and milk until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in pumpkin and pie spice.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill.
Garnish with gingersnaps, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Boil eggs and set aside.
Divide sausage into 6 portions; roll each egg in flour and with hands, press portion of the sausage around egg.
Dip sausage wrapped eggs into beaten eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Heat oil to 350°; cook each egg in oil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: cream cheese and anchovy spread
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature so it will be soft. Force Roquefort through strainer with wooden spoon.
With spoon mash Roquefort and cream cheese together until blended. Drain anchovies and chop fine.
Beat into cheese with brandy to taste, so anchovies are well blended and distributed.
Put into container and cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight or for a couple of days. Serve as a spread with bland crackers or another appropriate accompaniment.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: crochet starch
directions: Place the ingredients over low heat; stir until clear, not sugary.
Don't let mixture boil!
Let cool.
Wet crochet with water, then blot excess moisture with a towel, then dip in mixture.
Shape and let dry.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and dissolve cocoa over low heat in medium size pan.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt. Gradually add eggs to dry ingredients, one at a time.
Mix well. Gradually stir in vanilla and melted butter.
Beat by hand 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts if you wish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in a greased cookie sheet.
Remove from oven and spoon marshmallow cream over it.
When it starts to melt, gently smooth over cake.

title: chicken helene(makes 4 servings)
directions: Dust chicken with seasoned flour.
Melt 4 tablespoons of the butter in a shallow baking dish.
Place chicken, skin side down, in pan and bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Peel oranges.
Put peeling and cranberries through food grinder.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add orange sections, cranberry mixture, celery, pineapple and pecans; mix well.
Pour into a 10-cup mold; chill until set.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.
Make 2 days before serving.

title: pot pie
directions: In 3 quart, oblong baking dish, combine soups, milk, thyme, and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Top with biscuits.
Bake 15 minutes, or until biscuits are golden.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl, beat at medium speed for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan (10-inch or fluted) for 45 to 50 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly, cool 25 minutes in pan, then invert onto serving plate.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and shake well.

title: kolacky(in water)
directions: Combine water and yeast. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until dough is smooth or until dough works clean from hands. Wrap in towel and put in cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle board with powdered sugar and roll out dough. Cut into squares and fill with favorite filling.

title: chicken rub
directions: Mix and rub on chicken and bake as usual.
Bake a whole chicken about 2 hours.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook and thoroughly drain potatoes.
In mixer, whip cream cheese and half and half.
Slowly add potatoes.
Whip and add butter and seasonings.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made several days ahead and stored in refrigerator until 30 minutes before serving time.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and sugar.
Slowly add hot milk and vanilla.
Pour into custard cups and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in pan of hot water until the custards are firm or a knife blade inserted comes out clean.
Baking time, 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place squash and onion in a large skillet.
Pour in just enough water to cover bottom of skillet. Cover with a lid and cook over low heat until squash is tender, about 5 minutes; drain well.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in sugar, buttermilk, flavoring, butter and coconut.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: aunt mammie's cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and old bread and mix together.
Add onions, seasoning, eggs and enough broth or milk to make it slushy.
Bake at 350° until upon inserting a knife, it comes out clean.

title: swiss chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with cheese.
Mix soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing on top; drizzle melted butter on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 cup flour and butter into crumbly mass and pat into a shallow 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Let cool.
Beat sugar and eggs together; add vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Mix thoroughly and spread over bottom layer.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: husband's delight coconut pie
directions: Cook on top of stove.
Add coconut last.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crackers in pan. Place other ingredients in layers into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato and egg casserole
directions: Mix eggs and milk. Place frozen potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish. Add layer of sausage. Pour egg mixture over top. Cover with grated cheese. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: essence
directions: Mix together and use as a seasoning.

title: mocha cooler
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender container.
Cover and process at the highest speed until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in casserole.
Mix next 4 ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover. Add pineapple and green pepper.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: lemon loaves
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda. Alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk to the egg mixture. Stir in zest and nuts.
Pour in 2 greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Put margarine and milk on top. Do not mix!
Put in microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes (until butter is melted).
Stir until mixed well and thick.
Spoon on foil.
Place pecans on top.
Allow to cool.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix butter and pecans and roast.
Mix all other ingredients; add roasted pecans and put into ice cream freezer and churn. Yield: 4 qt.

title: marinated meat
directions: Pour sauce over meat and let marinate for at least 2 to 3 hours.
Cook meat on a grill or bake in the oven.
Serve with white barbecue sauce, regular barbecue sauce, honey and mustard or any kind of sauce that you can.
Makes a very good meal.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly (sticks very easily to saucepan).
Excellent for deviled eggs, ham sandwiches, potato, macaroni, egg and tuna salad.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix eggs and Milnot together. Tear bread into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
You may substitute sausage for cubed ham, bacon pieces or meat of your choice.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and salt.
Blend well, add milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until custard is done.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in next five ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 12 inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions, except add 1/2 can onions.
Spoon around outer edge of casserole.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour enough batter to make size of pancakes desired onto greased griddle and bake.
Temperature should be approximately 400°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Place pears, peaches, pineapple and cherries in casserole. In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and curry powder. Spread over top of fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour. Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: cream cheese pinwheels
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Spread thinly on tortillas, covering entire surface. Roll up jelly roll style and refrigerate. When set, slice into pinwheels and serve with picante sauce on the side.

title: caramel apple walnut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Add walnuts to reserved crumb mixture.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring 1 Coke to a boil and add jello.
Then pour the other Coke in cold.
Add 1 cup pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: super moist raisin-oatmeal cookies
directions: Place raisins and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil about 3 minutes on low heat.
Set aside to cool.
Do not drain.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into small chunks.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Grate cheese.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until well-blended.
Press into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over crust.
Freeze 15 minutes.
Swirl together ice cream and peanut butter.
Spoon into crust.
Drizzle with syrup.
Freeze at least 4 hours.

title: crackered pork chops
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Dip pork chops in egg mixture and then into crushed crackers.
Brown lightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pulled mints
directions: Boil sugar, water and butter to a hard ball stage.
Add flavoring.
Turn onto wet platter.
Cool; pull until brittle. Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Place in dish of powdered sugar.
Leave until mints become creamy.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Make a layer of scrambled beef, a layer of sliced potatoes and a layer of onions.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Cook, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dressing for cucumbers
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, salt and black pepper well. Pour over cucumbers.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine oleo, honey, mustard and curry powder.
Roll chicken breasts in this sauce and place in a single layer in a casserole dish.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.
Baste often and turn once.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter in large bowl.
Add sugar and beat.
Add honey and beat.
Add eggs and beat.

title: turkey salad
directions: Add ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve on lettuce. Great for sandwiches also.

title: campfire angel food
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Cut bread into 2-inch cubes.
Place on skewers.
Dip in condensed milk and then coconut.
Toast over coals until coconut is toasted.

title: deviled ham rolls
directions: Mix deviled ham and olives; chill until firm.
Shape mixture into 4 rolls.
Blend cream cheese, softened, and prepared mustard. Spread over rolls.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: elizabeth's sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, measure all ingredients except sprinkles.
Mix at medium speed and beat ingredients until well mixed.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Shape dough into a ball; wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets. Roll 1/2 to 1/3 of dough at a time; keep rest refrigerated.
Roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and cut into shapes.
Re-roll trimmings and cut.
Place cookies 1/2-inch apart; "sprinkle" and cook 8 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: herbed cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Remove bread crusts.
Spread cheese mixture on bread.
Cut sandwiches into desired shapes. (Parsley, basil, watercress, chervil and chives in any combination are good with this.)

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix soup and gelatin in a pan.
Warm.
Set aside to cool. Blend cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix in shrimp, celery and soup. Pour into mold and chill.
Spread on crackers.

title: mama pick's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beat in milk, flour and vanilla.
Bake in layers in greased and floured pans in 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Remove and set aside 1/2 cup corn bread mix. Combine remaining mix with 1/2 cup butter until crumbly. Put into the bottom of a baking dish. Mix together squash, green pepper, onions, sour cream and soup. Pour over corn bread mixture. Top with reserved corn bread mix. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bits of heaven
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Make little balls and bake 325° for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and shake in paper bag with powdered sugar.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by approximately 1 spoonful onto foil lined cookie sheet. Refrigerate until they are hardened.

title: spoonbread tamale pie
directions: Saute meat, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, salt, chili powder and pepper; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in corn meal, blended with the water; simmer 10 minutes.
Add olives and turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread Topping over meat.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° to 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add crushed pineapple; mix in sugar and flour. Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: In 2-quart pan boil potatoes and onions in water until tender but not mushy.
Do not drain.
Add other ingredients, except bacon, and simmer for 10 minutes.
Brown bacon and add little flour for thickening.
Add to soup.

title: home-made butterfingers
directions: Spread peanut butter between Cheese Nips. Dip in melted chocolate and let cool on wax paper.

title: world's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda in a small bowl. Combine margarine, sugars, vanilla and pudding.
Mix in a large bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add in flour mixture. Batter will be stiff. Add chips. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: black walnut taffy
directions: Butter cookie sheet and spread walnuts evenly over pan.
Mix other ingredients together in medium saucepan and bring to hard ball stage, stirring constantly.
Pour over walnuts when cool. Break into pieces.

title: alicia's crunchy two-style chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crush cornflakes in a plastic bag and dump them in a pie tin.
Wash and dry the drumsticks.
In a small frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Roll the drumsticks in butter.
Roll the drumsticks in cornflakes.
Put the rolled drumsticks in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and seasoned salt.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add milk.
Fold in mixed sugar and flour. Add corn.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Add mixture and stir a little.
Bake in oven at 350° until firm in center (about 45 minutes).

title: summertime pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles as directed on individual label (usually 7 to 8 minutes). Rinse with cold water and drain. Place in the fridge until ready to use.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Boil raisins and water together for 3 minutes.
Add milk. Scald, but do not boil.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add to raisin mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Add beaten egg yolks mixed with a small amount of milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes. Pour into baked pie crust.

title: humdingers
directions: Cook dates, margarine and sugar over medium heat for 9 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Dip in powdered sugar.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage until crisp-tender.
Melt fat or margarine in large skillet with lid.
Add cabbage.
Cook until all liquid is gone and cabbage just starts to brown, stirring occasionally.

title: marinated rice
directions: Thinly slice green onions (including tops).
Combine with white rice, finely chopped tomatoes, olive oil and vinegar. Cover and chill.

title: spongy gingerbread
directions: Mix all together and add last 1/2 cup boiling water.
Bake in 11 x 7-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour
into
deep pie pan.
Chill 45 minutes; save 1/2 cup for top of pie.

title: blueberry casserole dessert
directions: Put berries in buttered casserole.
Pour lemon juice over. Mix oleo, 1/2 cup of sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, milk, flour and baking powder.
Pour over berries.
Mix and sprinkle over top 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water over top and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix well and shape into balls. Place in baking dish and pour 2 1/2 cups tomato juice over balls. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Best if simmered awhile.

title: beefeater pie
directions: Add warm water to croutons; mix and press into buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Scramble hamburg and onion; drain off fat. Add cheese, eggs, catsup or barbecue sauce and cup of croutons. Press onto crouton crust.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake 2 minutes longer.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce. Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagna; top with some sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing lasagna pieces into cheese mixture.
End with a final layer of lasagna. Pour remaining sauce over, making sure all lasagna pieces are covered with sauce.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan. (Do not be concerned with the empty space at the ends of the pan; during cooking, the lasagna will expand and take up most of the area.)
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.
Let stand about 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter in large mixing bowl. Mix well. Put in casserole dish and divide butter into pats to place on top. Bake covered at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Prepare stuffing mix per package directions.
Combine ground beef, soup mix, ketchup, egg and water in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 of ground beef mixture into casserole dish. Spread stuffing mixture evenly over beef mixture.
Top with remaining beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, remove cover and bake for additional 15 minutes until top of loaf is brown.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch, vinegar and pineapple in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Watch carefully.
This will burn quickly.
Cool completely!
Once cooled, add all remaining ingredients.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies in food processor or blender.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 2 small packages chocolate instant pudding,
milk and Cool Whip.

title: chicken - shrimp supreme
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add mushrooms and saute. Add onions and saute 5 minutes.
Add soup and gradually stir in sherry and light cream.
Add cheese and heat on low, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Heat to serving temperature.
Stir in parsley before serving.
Serve over rice. Freezes well.

title: "esther saners" apple cake
directions: Blend together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt, then add margarine and mix until fine.
Beat eggs with water and mix with fork.
Put all ingredients together; mix until dough is formed. Press with fingers into cake sheet/cookie sheet.
Cut apples into 1/8ths and place into rows on dough.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and a little nutmeg; sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are soft.
Makes sheet cake (cookie sheet) size (10 x 15-inches) plus a small one.

title: beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large casserole/pot with lid to fit. Mix well.
Cover.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: quickie carrots
directions: Put brown sugar into small skillet and stir in ginger.
Add carrots and margarine and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes. Serve while good and hot.

title: cottage pudding with sauce(a good after-dinner dessert)
directions: Bake at 425° about 15 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients, then add liquids and beat.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Put oil in a pot or skillet over medium heat. Add flour; stirring until just brown. Stir in broth. Reduce heat to low and let simmer until thickened. When thickened add the chopped giblets or eggs. Add salt and pepper if needed.

title: quiche lorraine(microwave)
directions: Crumble bacon into small pieces.
Reserve 1 teaspoon of bacon and
teaspoon
of
onion slices for topping.
Spread bacon
and onions
evenly
in
bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle grated	cheese over bacon and onions.
In a 2-cup micro-proof measure, heat milk on High setting for 3 minutes.
Mix mustard in
beaten
eggs. Gradually
add
hot milk as you stir.
Pour carefully
into pie shell.
Sprinkle reserved bacon and onions on
top.
Cook
on
70 (Roast)
for 12 to 14 minutes or until center
is
barely set. Let stand for 20 minutes before serving.

title: chicken casseroles
directions: Combine all the ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Note:
If using beef consomme soup, add 1 can of water.

title: irish potato pudding(a corn shucking dessert)
directions: Mix together all ingredients; place in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, then, with a spoon, pull cooked edges from sides of pan and allow uncooked portion to fill in around the edges.
Continue to cook for 30 more minutes, or until firm consistency is obtained.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp stuffed roll-ups
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in butter, cook shrimp until shrimp turn pink.
Stir in crumbs, dill and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Spoon shrimp mixture onto center of each fillet; roll up. Secure with toothpicks.
In cleaned skillet over high heat, heat to boiling the fillets, wine, water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove fillets to warm platter.
Remove toothpicks; keep fish warm until needed.

title: zucchini zita
directions: Saute onions in hot butter for 2 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except for zita.
Cook and cover over low heat for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Zucchini slices should be tender but still retain their shape.
Serve over cooked zita.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Empty cake mix into 13 x 9 pan.
Pour peaches (with juice) over cake mix.
Stir lightly.
Dot with butter, cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Put rice and broccoli in large bowl.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave and pour over rice and broccoli.
Add soup, warm water and mushroom pieces.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Pour over all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into medium mixing bowl.
Whirl remaining ingredients in blender to form an emulsion.
Add to dry ingredients and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon into lightly buttered and floured 9-inch square pan and bake in preheated oven (350°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand in pan for 5 minutes.
Loosen edges with spatula and turn out onto cookie rack covered with wax paper.
Cool to room temperature before cutting.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of greased casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: tea syrup
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes, then pour on tea leaves and lemons.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight.
Strain and put in jar in a cool place.
Use 2 tablespoons in a glass of water.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion; drain off excess fat.
Mix with remaining ingredients in kettle or crock-pot.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: caramel pudding cake(early 1900's recipe)
directions: Boil and cool 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup water.
Pour into ungreased baking pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Beat all together.
Drop by teaspoons on sugar and water in pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake until cake floats away from sides of pan.
Cool until lukewarm.
Serve with whipped cream. (Nuts and whipped cream may be omitted.)
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mix with toothpick.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: very easy peach cake
directions: Pour peaches and juice into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over peaches.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Cover with slices of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.
Delicious served with ice cream!

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Pour meat into bottom of casserole dish.
Alternate layers of mushroom soup and vegetable beef soup. Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.
Serve with hot buttered rolls.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and cocoa in a saucepan over med. low heat.
Let this come to a rolling boil for 2 min. while stirring. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted, add oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper and let cool.

title: cheesy pizza pockets
directions: Heat oven to 425°. In a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until beef is no longer pink; drain well. Season with salt and pepper; stir in cheese and sauce. On a lightly floured surface, unroll pizza dough. Cut into 6 sections. Divide and spoon filling into center of each section. Bring together 4 corners of each rectangular section, pinching to seal. Loosely close straight edges of dough to form pockets. (It's not necessary to seal edges completely.)
Carefully transfer to ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato delight
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese, and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese and bake until melted.

title: lemon curd
directions: In the top of double boiler, melt the butter.
Stir in the lemon rind, juice and sugar.
Beat the eggs and yolks together until thick.
Blend into lemon mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, over hot water until mixture is very thick.
Chill before using.
For those who dislike lemon pies rigid with cornstarch.
Makes enough for 9-inch pan.
Can be used as a cake filling or in place of jam.

title: terri's peach pie
directions: Put peaches in bowl.
Stir in sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust and seal.
Cut vent in top crust.
Brush top crust with water.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until crust is done.

title: butter crisp garlic rolls
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in egg.
Add flour mixture.
Press dough into prepared pan.
Blend garlic, salt and butter.
Dip sharp knife into butter, then cut lengthwise and crosswise at 1-inch intervals.
Brush with remaining mixture; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: the dove's nest white chili
directions: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook until onion begins to soften, 3 to 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer. Do not brown. Add tomatoes, tomatillos and jalapeno. Cook until tomatillos are soft. Add chicken stock, green chilies, cooked chicken, oregano, cumin, cilantro, beans and lime juice. Heat through and season to taste with salt and pepper. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn bread with cheese
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Heat pan first, then spray with Pam. Bake at 400° in preheated oven until brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the corn flakes and 1/2 cup butter.
Line a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan with potato mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup butter and corn flakes.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Place crushed pineapple on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Alternate other ingredients except shortening which is added last.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be served with whipped topping, if desired.

title: poke salat(a famous southern dish served with pinto beans and cornbread.)
directions: Wash and parboil poke salat.
After parboiling, drain and put into hot Wesson oil in iron skillet; salt and pepper.
After tendering, add beaten eggs and finish cooking.

title: christmas morning brunch(must be prepared ahead)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in croutons.
Spread cheese over croutons.
Layer sausage over cheese.
Blend in eggs, 2 1/2 cups of milk and mustard.
Pour over layers.
Let set in refrigerator overnight or at least 2 hours.
Blend soup and other 1/2 cup of milk together and spread over rest after it set.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 300°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° if glass casserole or 375° if metal pan for 1 hour.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Cook on medium heat, then pour cake mix into the pudding mix; beat until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour the package of butterscotch morsels over the top of the cake.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Add melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar.
Add egg, lemon peel and lemon juice and mix well. Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle top with the 2 tablespoons of graham cracker crumbs. Cool, cut into bars and store in refrigerator.
These bars will freeze well.

title: tropical sunshine cake
directions: Combine cake mix, canned milk and eggs. Beat on low speed for 2 minutes. Stir in 1 cup of pineapple. Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Pour batter into pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until done. Cool for at least 15 minutes. Combine sugar and 2 tablespoons reserved juice in bowl and mix until smooth. Spread over warm cake. Sprinkle with coconut and remaining pineapple.

title: bar cookies
directions: Spread crescent rolls in 13 x 9 pan.
Cover with Eagle Brand milk and coconut pecan frosting mix.
Pour butter on top of mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: impossible ham 'n swiss pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 x 1/2-inch pie plate. Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high, or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate over ham and cheese mixture.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop-rice casserole
directions: Place rice in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix together soups and milk.
Pour over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over soups.
Top with pork chops.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes to brown chops.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pimiento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Grind in food chopper the cheese, pimiento and boiled eggs. Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: banana split torte
directions: Melt one stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush 3 cups vanilla wafers.
Mix with butter and pack well in pan; refrigerate well.
Beat at high speed until creamy the powdered sugar and soft butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Spread mixture on cracker crust. Slice bananas oblong.
(Let them sit in pineapple juice to prevent browning.) Place them on mixture.
Drain pineapple and place on bananas.
Place cherries on top of pineapple; top with Cool Whip.
(Optional:
top with 1/4 cup chopped nuts.)
Chill overnight or 4 hours.

title: diabetic jello
directions: Put 4 cups of water on stove to boil.
Dissolve the Knox gelatine in sauce dish with 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix and set aside.
Put Kool-Aid and sweetener in large bowl; add the boiling water to Kool-Aid mixture.
Add Knox gelatine mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add the cold water and refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours.

title: nine-day slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Pour over cabbage mixture. Cool. Cover and refrigerate.

title: ben's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook on medium heat for about 2 hours.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Put fruit in casserole.
In boiler, heat remaining ingredients until thick and bubbly.
Pour over fruit and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fall harvest apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix remaining ingredients, except apples and margarine.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Place top crust, that has slits cut in it, over the filling, unfold and trim overhanging edge of pastry 1-inch from rim of plate.
Fold and roll top edge under lower edge.
Cover with 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil during the last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: sugar-free date nut pie
directions: Soak dates in 1/2 cup water for 1 hour.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat.
Stir in milk, egg, nutmeg and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift and mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Beat 1 minute with spoon.
Avoid overbeating.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: On a plate, mix bread crumbs with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Dip beef into beaten egg, then into bread crumbs.

title: country-fried steak
directions: Blend baking mix, salt, pepper and paprika.
Coat meat pieces. (Reserve remaining seasoned mixture.)
Cook meat in hot shortening until brown.
Add 1/4 cup of the water.
Cover and cook over low heat about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to platter.
Add 1 cup of water to drippings in skillet.
Stir together 2 tablespoons of the reserved seasoned mixture and remaining 1/4 cup of water.
Gradually stir into drippings.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour over meat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: all fruit dessert
directions: You may use any type fruit.

title: hot chili recipe
directions: Stirring occasionally, cook slowly for 1 hour.
Brown 2 pounds of chuck (ground) or deer (ground) meat.
Add to mixture.
Then add:

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Cut beef steak into strips.
Combine soy sauce, 2 teaspoons oil, sugar and cornstarch and stir into strips.
Heat remaining oil in large skillet, add garlic, ginger and pepper pods.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add red bell pepper and corn, stir-fry 1 1/2 minutes. Add pea pods, stir-fry 30 seconds.
Remove vegetables; reserve. Stir-fry beef strips (1/2 at a time) 2 to 3 minutes.
Return vegetables and beef to skillet and heat.
Serves 4. Good served with rice.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Makes one pie. Recipe can be doubled.

title: six week muffins
directions: Make pie crust for two 9-inch pies or prepared crusts.

title: microwave granola
directions: Cook oats at Medium-high for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir often. Melt together butter, honey, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add nuts, seed, sugar, wheat germ and coconut.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook 6 minutes on Medium-high.
Add 1/3 cup raisins.
Cook 2 minutes. Stir often.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Store in glass jars.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: A surprise cobbler; batter rises to top during cooking forming a golden crust.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Blend butter, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat in the egg.
Stir in flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over jars.
Seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, pour Minute rice, margarine and chicken broth. Stir well to melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: colossal cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside. Combine flour and sugar; add milk and almond extract. Stir until blended. Spoon batter over butter; do not stir. Spoon cherries over batter; do not stir. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown. Yield about 8 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine in large bowl the margarine, salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over potatoes in greased bowl. Cover with cornflakes and margarine.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Beat Dream Whip as directed on package.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese.
Add this to Dream Whip plus powdered sugar and beat until fluffy.
Spread over graham cracker crust and top with favorite fruit pie filling.
Chill overnight.
Delicious.

title: flour icing
directions: Boil flour and milk until thick.
Cover with wax paper and cool.
Beat oleo or Crisco and sugar until whipped fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour mixture into this.
Beat until smooth.

title: yellow rice
directions: Saut onion; add broth and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix
together
oil,
dill
weed,
lemon
pepper, garlic powder and
dressing.
Pour
over
crackers.
Place on cookie sheet or deep
pan and place in 200° oven for 20 minutes; mix intermittently. These are much better if let sit in Tupperware with lid 2 or 3 days.

title: chicken in a bag
directions: Combine salt, oil and spices, etc.; let sit for 30 minutes. Rub entire inside and outside of chicken with oil mixture.
Place in a heavy brown bag and fold bag closed.
Bake in a roasting pan for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325° or until done.
Open bag last 1/2 hour to let brown.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients, except pineapple, to a boil.
Then add pineapple.

title: purple cow
directions: In a chilled glass, combine two scoops of ice cream and enough grape Nehi to flavor.
Blend until creamy, if desired.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook onion in margarine until tender. Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: indian pudding
directions: Heat 3 cups of milk in saucepan.
In a double boiler, combine cornmeal, salt, ginger, cinnamon and remaining milk.
Pour in heated milk, stirring to combine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Reduce heat to simmer water.
Cook 25 minutes, stirring frequently. Grease a deep 1-quart dish.
Remove bowl from heat; stir in butter and molasses until mixture is smooth.
Stir in eggs.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm.

title: pretzel garlands(ornaments for birds)
directions: Weave ribbon through pretzels to make an edible garland for the birds.

title: frosted oatmeal squares(microwave)
directions: Mix oats, sugar, oleo and syrup thoroughly.
Divide mixture between two 2-quart glass baking dishes (8 x 8-inch).
Press evenly into dishes and pack each.
Place in microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, until bubbly over entire top.
Cool.
Melt chips and peanut butter in a 1-quart bowl for 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Mix until smooth and spread over oatmeal mixture.
Store in refrigerator.
(The squares will seem hard to cut, but will soften at room temperature after a few minutes.)

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook slowly until thick, like jelly, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into baked shell. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: potato salad stack-up
directions: Combine potatoes and peas.
Toss tuna with dill weed.
Layer lettuce, potato mixture, tomato, tuna mixture and cucumber in 3 1/2-quart salad bowl.
Top with 1 1/2 cups Dill Sauce.
Cover; chill.
Serve with remaining Dill Sauce.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine milk and sugar over medium heat and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and stir. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let them harden.

title: best-ever piccalilli
directions: Quarter tomatoes and green and red peppers.
Put through food chopper, using medium blade; drain.
Place vegetables in large kettle.
Add vinegar; boil 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain and discard juice.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease pan and sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts.
Put all cake ingredients into large bowl; beat at high speed 6 to 8 minutes. Alternate batter and filler into thirds in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: date mini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dates, oil, baking soda and water.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add sugar, flour and egg.
Stir until just moistened.
Pour into 3 greased 5 5/8 x 3 1/4 x 1 7/8-inch mini loaf pans.
Bake in oven 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Chop tomatoes; chop onion, tops and all. Add remaining ingredients. Chill overnight or several hours.

title: chicken potato broccoli toss(serve hot or cold)
directions: Halve or quarter cooked potatoes.
Cut cooked broccoli into 2-inch pieces.
Mix everything and sprinkle walnuts over the top. Serve hot or cold.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended smooth, but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft, but not brown.
Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick, continue stirring.
Add seasonings and cheese which have been cut into small pieces.
Stir until melted.
Combine with cooked spinach. Serve immediately or put in casserole topped with bread crumbs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In frying pan, simmer butter, celery and onion until soft. Add broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is soft.
Add all other ingredients until cheese is melted.
Add rice; stir and serve.

title: zucchini pie
directions: One teaspoon cinnamon may be used instead of apple pie spice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in saucepan.
Add syrup, butter and salt. Warm
over	low heat until butter is melted.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Stir
into
sugar mixture.
Turn into pie shell and sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until filling is set in center.
Cool before serving.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Bring to a boil the first 5 ingredients.
Let cool.
Mix well the remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Add above mixture into flour and sugar mixture. Grease 5 (16 ounce) cans (beans or pears) and fill 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool on rack, empty out and wrap in foil.
Keeps well. Delicious for coffee time.
Try spread of butter.

title: della robia cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix as directed on the box label, except add grated lemon peel along with the cake flour mixture.
Bake and cool according to directions.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cake mix, peanut butter, Crisco oil, water and the eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drop from a teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork that has been dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: warm vegetable dip
directions: Mix and place in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Blend in blender or sift 3 times.
Store room temperature. Use 6 ounces boiling water to 1 1/2 tablespoons mix.

title: mixed fruit
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix all fruit together.
Combine pudding mix with fruit juice and toss with fruit mixture.
Refrigerate, then serve.

title: sunil's cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and onion.
Dice vegetables and toss together in bowl.
Add yogurt and season to taste with salt.
Serve well chilled.

title: quick and easy cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Add in whipped topping.
Add chocolate chips if desired.
Spoon into pie crust shell.
Chill 3 hours.

title: shrimp and cream cheese
directions: Cut the cheese
in
half
lengthwise
while still cold. Put on a plate and
let
soften.
Pour the cocktail sauce over the cream cheese and
sprinkle the shrimp over the top.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef in margarine.
Add next 5 ingredients, 1 1/2 cups hot water, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cook, covered, 1 1/4 hours; stir often.
Remove bay leaves; add vegetables.
Cook, covered, 30 to 45 minutes. Drain; reserve liquid.
Skim fat.
Add water to liquid to equal 1 1/4 cups; return to Dutch oven.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; stir into hot liquid.
Cook and stir until thickened; stir in beef and vegetables.
Heat through.
Serves 8.

title: empanadas
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper about 5 minutes in skillet; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper. Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Place 1 unfolded pie crust at one end of cookie sheet, greased.
Place 1/2 of beef mixture on half of pastry round.
Leaving 1-inch border; press edges together to seal and brush pastry with yolk mixture. Repeat with remaining crust at other end of cookie sheet.
Bake preheated at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cut in half.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 6 pieces.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and pecans or raisins.
Shake in a bag.
Place half of biscuits in Bundt pan and cover with half of sugar mixture.
Layer again with biscuits and sugar mixture.
Boil margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over cake and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat on medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour, sweet milk and vanilla; beat 3 minutes.
Spray 3 cake pans with Pam.
Pour batter into pans. Bake at 325° or 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chops and mushrooms
directions: Season	pork
chops
with
salt
and pepper.
Dredge in flour and
brown	slowly	on both sides.	Add diced onion and mushrooms over
pork	chops.	Mix cream of mushroom soup with water;	pour over
chops, onion and mushrooms.
Cover; simmer for about 25 to 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: italian meatball ragout
directions: Mix ground beef with egg, bread crumbs, basil, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Shape into small balls.
Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces; brown in large skillet.
Remove with slotted spoon; set aside.
Brown meatballs in pan drippings; remove and set aside with browned sausage.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone; add carrots, onion, green pepper, tomatoes and celery.
Return to pot and cook until tender.
Add potatoes, okra and chicken.
When cooked, brown a little flour and add to mixture.
Salt, pepper and serve.

title: mushroom hot dish
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place half the buttered bread squares on the bottom of the dish.
Place 1/2 the mushrooms on the bread.
Combine chopped celery, onion and green peppers with mayonnaise.
Spread half of this mixture over mushrooms.
Repeat layers.

title: baked beans
directions: Soften beans; soak in water overnight.
Simmer 1 hour.
Put beans in crock-pot and add all remaining ingredients along with the water.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 4 to 5 hours.

title: corn corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Bake in 425° preheated oven 20-25 minutes until done and golden.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, adding buttermilk last. Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until top is slightly brown for about 35 minutes.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan. Sprinkle with marshmallows and peanuts.
Break candy bars in half and place on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 1 minute, toss to coat.
Store in an airtight container.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.
Good with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: chinese beef and peppers
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic in oil in large skillet until meat is browned.
Add ginger, green pepper, bouillon, soy sauce and wine.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 5 cups or 4 servings, less than 350 calories each.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix on medium-high speed until smooth and creamy.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together in mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pour into a gallon ice cream freezer, adding milk to within 1-inch of the top of the freezer.
Makes 1 gallon of very smooth and delicious ice cream.

title: fudge puddles
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Add the flour, soda and salt to the creamed mixture. Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 40 balls, 1-inch each.
Place in lightly greased tassie pans.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and make wells in the center of each by gently pressing with melon baller. Cool 5 minutes; remove to wire racks.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: In saucepan, blend first 5 ingredients and heat until gelatin dissolves. Chill until partially set. Fold in remaining items. Arrange avocado slices in bottom of mold.
Pour gelatin mixture over and chill.

title: pepperoni squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: apple snicker salad
directions: Cut unpeeled apples and candy into bite-size pieces.
In a very large bowl mix pudding and milk with a whisk until combined. Fold in thawed topping.
Fold in apples and candy pieces.
Cover and chill in refrigerator 4 to 24 hours.

title: groundnut (peanut) sauce
directions: Cover chicken with water in a saucepan and gently boil with salt and onion; cook until chicken is tender.
Mix peanut butter gently with water until a thin paste is made.
Add peanut butter paste to chicken and broth.
Stir constantly and gently.
Add fresh tomatoes and chili powder to the chicken and cook gently for 30 to 40 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice, yam or fufu (African cassava root boiled and pounded).

title: sweet-sour venison
directions: Brown meat in oil and place in a covered roasting pan. Combine remaining ingredients and cover the steaks with this sauce.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes per pound, basting frequently, with the sauce.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in a greased casserole.
Top with paprika and more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican hats
directions: Place wontons in a muffin pan.
Bake 350° for 5 minutes. They will form crispy star-like cups.
Mix together all ingredients in a bowl.
Mixture should be moist but not soupy. Scoop mixture
into each cup using a heaping teaspoon.
Sprinkle top of mixture with a little shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and serve warm.

title: wayne's favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into loaf.
Bake in ungreased pan at 450° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoons about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: wafer cookies
directions: Mix
and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Sprinkle pecans
(chopped)	on top and press in.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in refrigerator. Better if made ahead of time.
Can be placed in graham cracker crust and served as pie (optional).

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in flour, 7-Up and lemon extract.
In greased pan, fold in batter.
Place in a cold oven at 325°.

title: ham-egg-brie strudel
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: jalapeno seasoned cornbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cook all at one time.
Cut in pieces and keep in freezer, if desired.
Heat and eat.

title: linguine salad
directions: Make sure linguine is dry.
Add all other ingredients and toss together.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Stays fresh for days.

title: fat free french dressing
directions: Dissolve gelatin in diet ginger ale in a blender.
Add vinegar, artificial sweetener, catsup, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, salt and lemon juice.
Blend at high speed until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a glass jar.
Add onion and garlic.
Shake well and refrigerate.
Let stand 3 hours before using.

title: peanut butter paisley brownies
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and brown sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to peanut butter mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Spread half the batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon syrup over top.
Carefully spread with remaining batter.
Swirl with spatula or knife for marbled effect.

title: stuffed crab
directions: Brown onions, bell pepper, garlic in margarine.
Add crab meat, bread crumbs, water and lemon juice. Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add parsley, sauces and seasonings. Place in shells or baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and brown quickly in 450° oven.

title: punch for 100
directions: Stir together and keep chilled.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour,
baking powder and salt.
Blend milk and egg together and add, gradually, to the dry ingredients.
Stir in corn.
Drop
by teaspoonfuls into hot, deep oil.
Cook 2 to 5 minutes until browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry what's it cake
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with miniature marshmallows. Prepare a yellow cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over marshmallows.

title: easy summer potatoes
directions: Potatoes can be peeled or unpeeled (whichever you prefer). Mix potatoes, peppers and onions in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with butter.
Season to taste.
Cover with foil.
Bake on top rack of gas grill until potatoes are tender, approximately 30 minutes. Great for summertime grilling.

title: microwave cream of broccoli soup
directions: Place butter in 2 quart microproof casserole and cook on High, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until melted.
Stir in flour and mix until smooth.
Blend in broth.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on High for 7 minutes.
Add broccoli and blend well.
Cover and cook on High for 15 minutes or until tender.
Let stand 10 minutes. Transfer soup to blender in batches and puree.
Return to casserole; cover and cook on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Beat half and half with egg yolk in small bowl. Add a little warm soup and blend well.
Beat mixture into remaining soup a little at a time; blend well.
Cook on Low for 1 to 2 minutes.
Garnish with lemon peel.

title: esther willingham's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add well beaten eggs.
Reserve 1 cup flour.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add cream and vanilla.
Mix.
Use the reserved flour on dough board when rolling out cookies.
Use a large cookie cutter.
Dough may be chilled for easier handling.
Bake at 425° on ungreased cookie sheet until edges are light brown.

title: luscious potato soup
directions: Heat oil in large soup pot.
Saute onions, carrots, celery and potatoes until onions are transparent.
Pour in stock, spices and salt.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for about 1 hour until the potatoes are tender, but won't fall apart.

title: tater tot casserole #1
directions: Place ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press onion into top of beef. Spread Tater Tots over beef. Mix soup and milk in bowl.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook broccoli and drain. Mix all together.
Add mushrooms.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine in frying pan.
Add diced onion and cook to soften (few minutes).
Add beef broth and uncooked rice. Stir, then pour into buttered casserole and bake 1 hour in preheated 350°
oven.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Beat cake mix, canned pudding and eggs 4 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle white sugar over the top of the cake. Sprinkle 1/2 package of butterscotch bits over to make the frosting.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: poor boy
directions: On a piece of foil, layer ingredients in the following order: 2 or 3 thin slices of potato, hamburger patty, thin slices of onions, thin slices of carrot, thin slices of potato and salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil and place in a baking dish. Bake at 325° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes (depending on oven) until done.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
In 8 x 12 pan, make layers of graham crackers and filling.
Warm frosting for 1 minute in microwave and spread over cake.	Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300° or 325°.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl from chilies down. Fold in chopped artichoke hearts. Spray pie plate with Pam. Spread mixture over bottom of pie plate. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 15-20 minutes until heated through, and browned.
Serve with crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the sausage.
Beat the eggs and combine with hash browns.
Mix together melted butter, milk and cheese.
Place all in a baking dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles
directions: Put cucumbers
and onions in jar in layers and pour remaining ingredients over layers.
Do not stir or beat.
Let stand in refrigerator for two or three days or as long as you like.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk; add Cool Whip and mix.
Layer graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layers of pudding mix, graham crackers, pudding mix, etc. (end with crackers on top).
Use ready made frosting and melt in microwave; spread on top of crackers. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight before serving.

title: tomato cheese fondue
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook tomatoes, onion and garlic for 10 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened, stirring often.
Stir in soup and mustard. Gradually add cheese, stirring until smooth after each addition. Pour cheese mixture into fondue pot and keep warm.
Serve with apple wedges.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: grandma mason's congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour melted butter over sugar.
Stir. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 10 x 15-inch greased and floured baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: the dip
directions: In a glass pie plate or other dish of similar size, spread the cream cheese in an even layer.
Next, spoon in the chili and spread it into an even layer.
Finally slice cheese and make a third layer with it.
Cover with clear wrap and microwave until heated, approximately 4 minutes.
Warm chips and sit in a circle around dip and dig in.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until mixture boils.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Mix well and bake for 25 minutes in microwave or bake in oven at 325° until dry.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Top assorted crackers with Monterey Jack cheese with jalapeno peppers.
Top with some salsa, if desired.
Broil for 30 to 60 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare pans.
Spread nuts and coconut in pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine; add sugar and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Pour over cake batter in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Lay burritos in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine chili and salsa.
Mix well.
Pour this mixture over burritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: hungry jack chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat brown sugar, sugar, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well. Set aside. Combine all dry ingredients; mix well. Add chocolate chips and nuts; combine to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Store in airtight container.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Combine barbecue sauce and preserves in a large skillet and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: fudge nougats
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in well-buttered 12 x 8-inch pan.

title: pear slices au chocolate
directions: In small microwave-proof bowl, place chocolate chips and shortening.
Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or just until chips are melted and smooth when stirred.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients. Roll out dough and cut.	Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: crispy crust baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts.
Remove skin, if desired.
Pat dry.
In bowl, beat egg and milk.
In a separate bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco, cream, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add 1/2 cup of flour at a time.
Add flavoring.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: molly's chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken, cut in pieces.
Put the pieces in a buttered casserole.
Now make a sauce of mushroom soup, sour cream and sherry.
Salt and pepper the chicken first and then pour sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
A nice brown crust will form over the top of the chicken.
Serve over white rice.

title: cheese and spinach pie
directions: Place Swiss cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle with spinach, mushrooms and meat. Mix next 4 ingredients together. Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 main-dish servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Measure sifted flour.
Add baking powder, salt, baking soda and spices.
Cream butter and add sugars gradually.
Cream well. Add eggs, one at a time; beat until light.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add pumpkin and nuts.
Mix well. Bake in 8-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt a little oleo and saute the celery, onion and green pepper until tender, but not brown. Cook mushrooms in a small amount of oleo.
Add 3 tablespoons oleo to celery and onion mixture. Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Slowly add chicken broth. Cook
until thick. Add sour cream, salt, pepper, pimento and chicken.
Mix thoroughly and put in a casserole sprayed with vegetable oil.
Sprinkle with cheese and add almonds.
Bake until heated through at 350°.
Can also add Parmesan or Romano on top. This can be frozen or prepared ahead.
Makes 8 servings.

title: aunt bessie's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Stop and scrape down sides of blender.
Mix until smooth and thick.
Store in icebox.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix.
Add water to equal 1 gallon.
Just before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add the remaining ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Put sauce on bottom (of loaf pan), then layer the tortillas, then layer of cheese.
Repeat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add dates, sugar and eggs. Cook over slow heat.
Stir constantly until mixture comes away from side of pan or makes balls.
Take off; cool slightly, then stir in Rice Krispies and nuts.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on a piece of wax paper.
Shape mixture into 2-inch rolls.
Chill.
Cut in slices.

title: apricot mumbles
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix oleo with sugar until smooth. Add flour, salt and baking soda; add oatmeal.
Press 1/2 of dough into pan.
Spread on jar of apricot filling.
Crumble remaining mixture over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheeses and dried beef.
Then add Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Make into a ball.

title: brass polish
directions: Mix. Wipe on brass. Dry off. Set in sun to dry and get hot. Then wipe down with tung oil and let dry. (using polish, will not have to polish so often.)

title: butterhorn rolls(never fail)
directions: Scald and cool the milk.
Add yeast that has been soaked in the warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir well. Add flour and stir well for 2 minutes with spoon.
Cover with towel and let rise in large mixing bowl, greased, until double or more in bulk.
Divide dough into 3 parts and roll 1/2-inch thick into "pie shape" on floured board.
Cut each pie shape into quarters, then each quarter in thirds.
Begin at large end and roll into rolls; place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.
Makes 36 medium size rolls.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: squash creole
directions: Slice and fry any summer squash.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Add 1 recipe Creole Sauce.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Turn into greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: homestyle chile(for the crock-pot.  makes 6 to 8 servings.)
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; cut into 1-inch cubes.
In slow cooker, lightly toss beef cubes and Kitchen Bouquet, coating meat on all sides.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on beef cubes; stir gently until evenly coated.
Add onion and green pepper.
Combine tomato juice, tomatoes, garlic, cumin and chili powder; pour over beef and vegetables.
Stir gently.
Cover; cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or until tender.
Add kidney beans during last hour.

title: good cookies
directions: Cream margarine in large mixing bowl. Beat in oil and egg. Sift together flour, salt, brown sugar, white sugar and soda. Beat in the top mixture and add vanilla. With wooden spoon, fold in crushed cornflakes, oatmeal and chopped nuts. Shape in small balls and place on greased cookie sheet and press with fork. Do not put too close to each other. Bake at 325° for approximately 15 minutes. Yield: 125 cookies.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts into coarse pieces; mix in mayonnaise and cheese.
Add onion and pepper, if desired.
Blend all ingredients; place in a small baking dish or loaf pan.
Serve hot with crackers.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour, or until top is lightly browned.

title: beef 'n bean barbecue bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Add beans, sauce, onion and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 pound cheese cubes.
Pour into a 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cut biscuits in half, forming circle.
Place, cut side down, around edge of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with additional cheese slices and return to oven until melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown sugar and can biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In pan, mix first 5 ingredients; stir until sugar and butter are melted.
Pour into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Separate biscuits; flatten to 3-inches oblong. Spread with peanut butter.
Twist biscuit 3 or 4 times.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes or until brown.
Let cool 3 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: roast beef
directions: Grease pot with bacon fat and fry the roast all around at high heat.
Put 2 cups hot water, black pepper and bay leaves into pot. Simmer for 3 hours.
Take roast out and when cold, slice it thin. Place in gravy and warm it up.

title: chiperoo bars
directions: Combine cooking oil and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
To the shortening mixture, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add pecans and chocolate chips; mix well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When almost cool, cut into bars.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes. Combine in bowl with 1/2 cup oleo. Season with salt, pepper, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup. Place in 3-quart casserole (or two 1 1/2-quart). Mix remaining oleo with corn flakes. Sprinkle over top. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fred's stromboli
directions: Roll out thawed bread dough on floured surface.
Place dough on a cookie sheet.
Cut peppers and onions into long strips.
Dice chicken.
Lay peppers and onions in middle of dough.
Top with Ricotta cheese and diced Mozzarella cheese; pour spaghetti sauce over all.
Pull dough together and bake at 375°.
Makes two 12-inch long stromboli.

title: baby meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together toughly. Form into small meatballs. Fry in hot oil until brown. For a dipping sauce, add 1/2 cup of catsup and 1/2 cup of Barbecue sauce together and mix well.

title: batter dinner rolls
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a pan.
Heat until oleo melts.
Add 1 cup cold water to heated mixture; stir and add yeast.
Then add egg and salt.
Stir in flour.
If needed, add more flour to get a bread-type dough consistency.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Shape into balls and place in greased pan; let the dough rise for 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 1 dozen rolls.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Beat cake mix (dry), pudding and pie filling (dry), milk, oil and egg whites in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan and spread evenly.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pan; turn upside down onto heatproof serving plate.
Remove pan; cool cake completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add rest of ingredients. Batter will be thin.
Pour in greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberries in port wine syrup
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, port wine and lemon juice with 1/2 cup water and bring to a simmer.
Remove from heat, pour into a bowl and cool.
Meanwhile, rinse, dry and hull strawberries.
Cut them in half or quarters if they are very large.
When syrup is cool, add berries and toss to coat.
Serve immediately or refrigerate up to 8 hours.
Return to room temperature before serving.
Serves 6.

title: sabrina's special
directions: Put all together and cook until done.
Add your own ingredients.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
If too thick, add water.

title: good and easy company chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken pieces and place in shallow casserole.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and put in 350°
oven for 30 minutes.
Combine mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Drizzle sherry over it all and return to oven for 30 more minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
For large groups, multiply all the portions and make your own king-size casseroles of heavy-duty foil placed on cookie sheets and cupped up around the edges.

title: chicken liver kabobs
directions: On skewers, alternate chicken livers, sprinkled with salt and pepper, folded half slices of bacon, mushrooms and stuffed olives. Grill kabobs over charcoal or broil indoors 2 to 3 inches from heat, turning occasionally until done.
To serve, rest skewer on plate.
Push off food.
Pass bottled meat sauce.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Combine next 5 ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat one minute on medium speed.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour mixture into three greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely before icing.
Spread frosting between layers and on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
In a separate bowl mix flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Mix wet and dry ingredients.
You may add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Cool on a rack.

title: garden zucchini cheddar bread
directions: Saute onion in margarine in a skillet until tender.
Cool slightly.
Combine with baking mix and next 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Stir in zucchini, Cheddar cheese and almonds.
Spread in a greased and floured 9-inch round baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Yield:
12 slices.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar.
Spread on crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Lay on cookie sheet, bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheddar cornsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400° or 425°.
Combine flour with cornmeal, baking powder, cheese and bacon.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl; beat well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until flour is moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full, or well-greased and heated heavy cornstick pans, filling almost full.
Bake muffins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes and cornsticks at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand a minute or two before removing from pans.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as stated on package.
Combine milk, cream of coconut and pineapple together.
Punch holes in top of cake while it is still hot and pour mixture over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and then sprinkle coconut over that.
Let cool and then place in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Saute chicken in a large skillet with water until tender.
