Add wine and apricots; cook for approximately 5 minutes more.
Bake in baking pan with Cheddar on top until cheese melts.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Salt and pepper chicken and arrange on top of rice.
Melt oleo and pour over chicken and rice.
Mix water and soups.
Pour over chicken.
Place in oven at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken with celery, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add eggs.
Carefully fold in mayonnaise; chill thoroughly.

title: easy quiche
directions: Sprinkle Swiss cheese, bacon and onion into a greased pie plate.
Mix together Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes until browned. Let set a few minutes before cutting.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Mix the white sugar and corn syrup and bring to a boil.
At the first bubbles, time for 1 minute.
Keep heat on high.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread in buttered cookie sheet.
Melt together and spread on top the chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Cut into squares.

title: tropical ham slices
directions: Place ham slice in roasting pan.
Spread top and sides with mustard and sprinkle with the brown sugar.
Chop apricots in blender (not too fine).
Add pineapple and liquids to apricots and mix well.
Pour over ham.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread ingredients in pan in order as listed.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mayonnaise, 3/4 cup cheese, crab seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and hot sauce.
Add crab meat.
Place mixture in ovenproof dish; top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with crab seasoning.
Bake about 15 minutes. Serve with your favorite crackers or bread pieces.

title: our family's favorite chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium saucepan, combine the first seven ingredients.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 2-quart casserole or 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits and arrange over the hot chicken mixture.
Brush each biscuit with margarine and sprinkle crushed croutons over the biscuits.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown on top.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery in 1 tablespoon shortening; drain off excess fat.
Mix meat with soup, vegetables with juice, noodles, soy sauce and mushrooms with juice.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Use large casserole.

title: bonnie's meat loaf dinner
directions: Mix beef, milk, basil, oatmeal, mustard, green pepper, onion, egg and catsup thoroughly.
Place mixture in large baking dish. Shape into donut shape.
Place mixed vegetables in center of ring. Add potatoes and any remaining mixed veggies to outside. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more to brown.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt, shortening and lightly beaten egg.
Fold in flour.
Roll out dough and cut out large size biscuits, folding them in half with patty of butter between fold.
Let rise 2 hours; then bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add condensed milk and beat again.
Add lime juice and food coloring.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust and refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream.

title: party mix
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large roaster.
Mix together last 5 ingredients and pour over cereal mixture, stirring occasionally, to coat all cereal.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Allow cream cheese, whipped topping and pina colada mix to melt a little so that they are easier to mix. Mix in sugar, if desired. Pour mixture into graham cracker crust. Chill overnight before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: In a medium size bowl, blend cream cheese, vanilla extract and lemon juice together, then add condensed milk.
Pour into crust. Let sit 10 to 15 minutes in refrigerator, then serve.

title: microwave scallops cacciatore
directions: Combine onion, green pepper, garlic and oil in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave for 3 minutes, uncovered.
Chop tomatoes and add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Microwave, covered, for 6 minutes or until scallops are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large pot, bring chicken stock to boil. In skillet, saute onion in butter; add thyme and wine. Boil 2 to 3 minutes. Add flour, stirring briskly with a whisk. Boil 2 to 3 minutes whisking constantly until smooth. Add 1/2 of the chicken stock. Cook on low for 10 minutes. Add remainder of stock, white pepper, nutmeg, cheese, cream and broccoli. Simmer for 10 more minutes or until broccoli is just done. Serves 6.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix together spread, put on French bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until melted.
Put under broiler until lightly browned.

title: vicki's chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken and cube.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Stir soup, gravy, butter sprinkles and chicken into noodles.
Season to taste with Mrs. Dash or seasoned salt.
Heat through.
Creamy, low-fat and delicious!

title: creamy tacos
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for a few minutes until cheese melts.
Cooks well in crock-pot.
Serve warm.

title: green beans with horseradish sauce
directions: Cook beans with meat and sliced onion for 1 hour or more. Blend mayonnaise with remaining ingredients and set aside at room temperature.

title: six layer dimes *
directions: Place in a 2-quart casserole:
potatoes, celery, beef, onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off grease.
Prepare potatoes as you would for meal.
Layer the ground beef, potatoes, cheese, ground beef, potatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° until it melts.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Garnish with pimento strips, if desired.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water and other ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs (well beaten).
Sift soda, cream of tartar and salt with the flour.
Add to mixture.
Mold into a loaf and place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice off or soften dough by leaving out in room temperature enough to roll out.
Cut in shapes desired.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: root beer float
directions: Take can of root beer and pour into large glass.
Then take 1 or 2 scoops of your favorite ice cream and put in the glass with root beer.
Add whipped cream and cherry and enjoy.

title: lillie's roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add salt, sugar and shortening. Mix well.
Add enough flour until dough is stiff.
Cover.
Set aside in a warm place until it doubles in size.
Knead dough on floured wax paper.
Shape or cut into rolls and place in a greased pan.
Let rise in a warm place.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: end of the garden pickles
directions: Mix water and salt; stir until dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers, peppers, cabbage, onion and tomatoes.
Soak overnight.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix following package directions.
Pour 2 cups batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, bake 15 minutes.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels and margarine with sweetened condensed milk, stirring until smooth. Spread evenly over cake, spread remaining cake batter over caramel mixture.
Top with nuts.
Return to oven, bake 30 to 35 minutes or longer until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool. Garnish as desired.

title: nut nuggets
directions: Cream shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and almond extract, mix well. Combine flour, soda and salt, stir mixture into creamed mixture. Chill or freeze dough.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls, roll in pecans.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Gently press in (cherry half) or (pecan half) into center of cookie.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine bread crumbs and milk in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in raisins.
Beat eggs and yolk together. Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Pour into bread and milk mixture; sprinkle with cinnamon on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Mix mayo, soup, eggs, cheese and Worcestershire sauce together.
Fold in broccoli.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix artichoke pieces, sour cream, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese; blend well.
Pour into a shallow baking dish; set aside.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine half and half, eggs and seasonings; mix well.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add cheese and bacon to the egg mixture.
Pour into a pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers; cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time while beating.
Add milk and wafers alternately.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Add vanilla.
Stir well.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour and 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken and asparagus medley
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pound chicken breasts; add seasonings to taste.
Cut bottoms off the asparagus, leaving them about 6 inches long (most tender part).
Lay breasts flat, then put 3 or 4 spears side by side in the center of each breast.
Spread 1/2 tablespoon margarine across the spears in each breast.
Fold chicken over like a jacket (overlap).
tags: Campbell's chunky cream of mushroom soup

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Warm milk.
Pour over cereal.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
(If you're worried about too much sugar, cut it down to 1/3 to 1/2 cup.)
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Place in a larger pan with an inch or two of water in bottom.
Bake 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated cabbage
directions: Mix grated cabbage, onion and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients together in a saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, mixing occasionally.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Make out in balls (small) and brown slightly.
Place in casserole and cover with sauce (recipe follows).
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add chopped onion.
Add eggs and salmon.
Form into patties or croquettes and fry until golden.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Saute first 3
ingredients
until
done
on medium-high (approximately 10 minutes).
Add
cream
cheese
to
center of pan, reduce heat and cook
5 minutes.
Stir and blend in cream cheese.
Set aside.
In
same skillet put 2 tablespoons margarine, broccoli, onion,
mushrooms
and soy sauce.
Stir-fry on high approximately 5 minutes just until color of onion/broccoli changes.
Add in chicken
and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in cashews if desired.

title: macaroni and chipped beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Tear beef in small pieces.
Combine beef, cheese, milk and soup in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add macaroni; combine thoroughly and top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant platter
directions: Cut eggplants evenly in half lengthwise.
With a knife, carefully remove eggplant meat to a bowl.
Be sure the eggplant shells are 1/2-inch thick.
Chop eggplant meat in bowl.
Add ground beef, tomato sauce, garlic salt, salt, pepper, oregano and green onions.
Mix thoroughly.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn; sprinkle with salt.
Melt butter in pan.
Cut marshmallows in quarters or use mini-marshmallows.
Alternate layers of popcorn and marshmallows in pan.
Cover; heat slowly, until marshmallows are partially melted.
Mix well; form into 2-inch balls.
Makes about 9.

title: sour cream cutout cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients.
Sift the four dry ingredients. Add together and chill 6 hours.
Roll out to 1/4 inch and use cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100.

title: sunday morning sausage and egg souffle
directions: Layer bread, then sausage and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour evenly over ingredients in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce nuggets
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt and spices.
Add nuts.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add baking soda to applesauce.
Add egg. Add to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in butterscotch pieces.
Drop by teaspoons two or three inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: triple-layer brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In top part of double boiler, over hot water (not boiling), melt 1 cup chocolate pieces.
In top part of another double boiler, melt butterscotch morsels.

title: buttermilk sopaipillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add buttermilk, then enough water to moisten all ingredients and form a dough that can be handled.
Roll dough out on floured surface until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut dough in 4-inch triangles.
Fry in deep oil heated to 400°.
Press sopaipillas under oil until they puff.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with honey.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: oreo pie
directions: Put cookie crumbs in bottom of oblong pan (reserve 1/2 cup). Mix pudding mix as directed and spread for next layer, then spread Cool Whip.
Top with half cup Oreo crumbs.
Chill before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350° to 375° until done.

title: shirley's caramel pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar and add 1/2 cup milk and mix well.
Beat egg yolks separately, then add to mixture.
Add remaining milk, butter, and vanilla.
Cook until thick (stir constantly).
Set aside.
Pour 1/2 cup sugar into small iron skillet and brown slowly.
Mix well into other mixture.
Pour into cooked pie shell; add meringue and brown.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples and run through sieve or food processor.
Add all ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Fill jars and place in hot water.
Boil to assure sealing of lids (30 minutes).

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Season with salt and pepper; drain.
Cook rice as directed.
Add hamburger mixture.
Stir in tomato juice, 1/2 or 3/4 of the can.
Do not make soupy.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
May also use macaroni instead of rice.

title: raspberry meringue squares* * * * *
directions: A friend in Colorado, who is a wonderful cook, gave me this recipe.
It really is as good as it is pretty.
At the time, walnut oil was very hard to find, but now it is very common.
The bread should be sliced, buttered, wrapped in foil and heated through before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle marshmallows over the bottom.
Combine strawberries, gelatin and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients; beat for 3 minutes.
Pour over marshmallows in pan; spread strawberry mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken and chokes
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika over chicken.
Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons butter.
Set aside in casserole.
Add 4 tablespoons butter to drippings.
Saute mushrooms.
Arrange chokes between chicken.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms.
Add chicken broth, sherry and rosemary.
Cook and stir a few minutes.
Add to casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 40 minutes or more.
Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sauce and 1 cup hot water until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry mix and pecans.
Pour 1/2 mix and chill.
Spread sour cream or cream cheese when thick. Add remaining mix.
Refrigerate.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease oblong pan.
Pour in pineapple.
Add blueberries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour in box of dry cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle on nuts and remaining sugar.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Wait at least 25 minutes to cut.
About midway during cooking time, cut slits in cake to allow juice to come to the top of the cake.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Mix rest of ingredients and cook.
When cooked, add cheese and sour cream to top of soup.
Serve with Tostado chips.

title: dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients except chocolate chips into a bowl and beat.
Blend in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar into bowl.
Add the shortening to flour mixture and blend together until of corn meal-like consistency.
Pour milk into flour mixture slowly.
Add the egg; stir to stiff dough.
Knead five times; roll and cut.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes. These biscuits can be cut out, placed on sheet and frozen, then baked as usual as needed.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put canned milk in pan of water unopened.
Bring water to a boil and boil for 3 hours, keeping can covered.
Let cool and then open.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix everything thoroughly, except tomato sauce, mushrooms and cheese.
Stir in 3/4 cup tomato sauce.
Press 1/2 meat mixture into a loaf pan.
Sprinkle on cheese and mushrooms.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Pour off excess grease; spread on remaining tomato sauce and bake for an additional 45 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water, add undrained pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Pour into individual molds or a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: stuffed tomatoes with chicken salad
directions: Scoop out seeds and membranes from tomatoes.
Season inside with salt.
Fill each tomato with chicken salad.

title: oven roasted carrots
directions: Place carrots, onions, and garlic in two greased 15x10x1-inch baking pans. Drizzle with oil and vinegar. Sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper; toss gently to coat. Cover and bake at 450° for 20 minutes; stir. Bake, uncovered for 10 minutes; stir again. Bake 10 minutes longer or until carrots are crisp-tender. 8 servings.

title: oven scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and salt and mix well.
Add bacon or cheese.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the oven. Add egg mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Stir several times.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine pineapple chunks, cheese, pineapple juice, flour and sugar.
Spoon into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and butter slices.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Melt shortening or butter in frypan.
Dice green pepper and onion. Saute in melted shortening until tender. Add ground beef and cook until brown (not hard).
Chop the cabbage and add to mixture. Add tomato sauce, water and desired spices. Bring to bubbling stage, then cut heat back to low or simmer.
Allow to cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
More water may be added.
If stew is sour, add sugar in small amounts.

title: taco casserole
directions: Place beef in a pan and brown; drain.
Stir taco seasoning mix into beef and let cool.
When cool, stir in the water and sour cream.
Add beans, lettuce, onion, chili peppers, tomatoes, olives, cheese and taco sauce.
Mix all together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: marinade for pork chops
directions: Mix together ingredients. Marinate pork chops for a couple of hours or more.

title: two finger cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream margarine, cocoa and sugar. Beat in egg. Add in one at a time and stir the baking powder, salt, black pepper, cinnamon, cloves and vanilla. Mix in flour. Roll into 3/4-inch balls. Place 1 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Flatten balls to 1/4-inch thickness with 2 of your fingers to make design. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 minutes. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Blend sugars, shortening and eggs together.
Stir well and add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Grate onion over hot potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and lemon juice.
Pour oil over potatoes slowly, stirring slightly with a fork.

title: frost-on-the-pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil, and eggs in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Combine dry ingredients; add to oil mixture, beating well. Stir in pumpkin.

title: sweet potatoes with pecans
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Combine with egg, 3 tablespoons butter, orange juice and salt.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in 1/3 cup pecans.
Place into buttered shallow casserole. Sprinkle remaining nuts and sugar over top and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well, measure out by rounded spoonfuls and flatten with floured fork.
Cook in oven at 350° until well browned around edges.
Makes 12 servings.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.

title: steak
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Coat meat.
Brown meat on both sides.
Add liquid.
Simmer on low heat for 2 hours.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup, then cool slightly.
Mix gelatin with warm water, then add to soup.
Mix mayonnaise with cream cheese and mix well; add chopped vegetables.
Add soup mix and crab.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into 5 1/2-cup mold.
Chill several hours.

title: vanilla cream cheese sauce for carrot cake
directions: In bowl of food processor or with electric mixer, whirl the butter for 2 or 3 seconds.
Add the cream cheese and whirl again briefly.
Add the powdered sugar and the vanilla; blend for a few seconds more.

title: hot mustard pickles
directions: Pack jars with cucumbers and spoon the remaining ingredients over top of filled jars.
Fill to the brim with vinegar.
Seal jars and set away for at least 2 weeks.
Don't process in any way. They have a strong enough brine that they won't spoil.

title: italian-style zucchini
directions: Cut ends off zucchini.
Boil in salted water for 5 minutes. Halve lengthwise.
Remove pulp with spoon; reserve shells. Combine zucchini pulp, crumbs, 1/2 cup cheese, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and eggs; mix well.
Fill shells.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough in greased pizza pan at 350° for 15 minutes. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Place on top of cooled crust.
Place pineapple on top of cream cheese mixture. Arrange fruit in a circle on top of pizza.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Pour all ingredients into a 5-quart pot slow cooker or crock-pot.
Simmer for 30 minutes to 4 hours.
The longer it cooks, the better.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to boil and pour over cucumbers which have been packed in hot jars with dill and garlic.
Seal immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Turn on broil last few minutes to brown on top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion 5 to 7 minutes in small amount of water. Drain and coarsely mash. Mix in other ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ham and bow tie pasta
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Melt butter.
Add pasta and then add remaining ingredients.

title: mounds
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients (mixture is stiff).
Form into small balls (rub hands with powdered sugar so they won't stick). Let balls stand 10 minutes or longer in refrigerator.
Melt chips and paraffin over low heat or in microwave.
Dip each ball in melted chocolate.
Let dry on waxed paper.

title: beet salad
directions: Combine and spread on top of salad.

title: jello mold
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the gelatins in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in the milk, pineapple with juice, mayonnaise, cottage cheese, nuts and horseradish sauce.
Mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Pour into an oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill overnight.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple.
Stir in dry jello.
Refrigerate.
This makes a delicious salad and will keep for several days.

title: easy meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix together beef, stuffing mix and seasoning packet and egg. Top with ketchup.
Microwave at High (10) for 15 to 20 minutes (temperature 170°).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: minnesota layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Cover with 1 cup mayonnaise to which you have added 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let sit 8 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Just before serving, smother with Parmesan cheese and top with crumbled bacon.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to oil, then eggs, pumpkin, spices, flour and other ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans, greased.
Fill pans halfway. Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, cooking until straw colored.
Place onion in bottom of a 4-quart casserole.
Arrange sliced potatoes over onion.
Sprinkle with a little salt and paprika.
Repeat same procedure using the tomatoes, rice and ending with the green pepper.
(Meanwhile brown the pork chops on both sides in skillet.) Arrange on top of peppers.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Add more water if necessary.
Cover.

title: soul "o" gratin
directions: Place margarine in 4-cup measure.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 20 to 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in flour, bouillon granules and nutmeg; stir in milk.
Microwave, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes, stirring every minute, until thickened; stir in Cheddar cheese.
Spread broccoli in square dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches; sprinkle with lemon juice.
If fish fillets are large, cut into 4 serving pieces; pat dry.
Arrange fish, thickest parts to outside edges, on broccoli; sprinkle with salt.
Spread sauce over fish and broccoli. Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 7 to 9 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 4 minutes, until fish flakes easily with fork.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.

title: chicken tortelinni
directions: In medium size saucepan bring chopped vegetables to a simmer in 2 c. chicken broth.
Cook until tender.
Bring to boil another 4 c. chicken broth, add tortelinni, cook until it floats.
Add chicken and vegetable mixture.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°.
While butter is melting, mix flour, sugar and milk by hand.
When butter is melted, pour flour mixture on top of butter, then your fruit. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until it is golden brown.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and sour cream to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 300°, then 15 minutes at 325°.
Do not open oven.

title: lemon tea cookies(very soft)
directions: Stir vinegar into milk; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat egg and flavoring.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk mixture, beating after each addition.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove at once from sheet.
Brush tops with Lemon Glaze.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender and drain.
Combine soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until cheese melts.
Combine with cabbage and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until margarine melts and bread crumbs are toasted.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken which is laid on top.
Dot with butter.
Cook in oven with top on for 30 minutes at 400°. Remove top and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken and salt and pepper it and put garlic powder to taste.
Arrange chicken in a large baking dish with skin side up. Dot with butter and sprinkle 1/3 cup flour over all.
Cover bottom of dish with water.
Bake uncovered in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Turn chicken over and add potatoes that have been peeled and quartered.
Add 1/2 cup of water and cover. Bake 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in small saucepan. Heat to boil and then simmer for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in large heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil and allow to boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme until blended.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or casserole dish.
Allow to cool, cut into squares when firm.
Makes 3 pounds of candy.

title: rosemary-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a large bowl, combine potatoes, oil, butter, garlic, salt, rosemary and pepper, mix well. Spread potato mixture over ungreased baking sheet. Roast, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender and lightly browned, about 50 minutes. Transfer to serving bowl, stir in parsley.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt in 9 x 9-inch square pan 1 stick butter,

title: nutty rice
directions: Spread rice on cookie sheet.
Place in preheated 400° oven. Stir every 2 minutes for 6 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Can be stored in airtight container in fridge.
To cook, boil or steam as usual.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix the flour, powdered sugar and butter together and pat into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minute at 350°.
Meanwhile, prepare rhubarb, sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well with rhubarb.
Pour these last ingredients into the baked crust.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.

title: party-time popcorn bars
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with foil so that foil extends over sides of pan; butter foil.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Take from heat and add 3 cups quick oatmeal and 1/3 cup peanut butter.
Drop on wax paper by spoonful.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Bring to boil; have at a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; stir well.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoon.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients for dressing. Mix dressing with all other ingredients.

title: raspberry-ros cooler
directions: Combine sherbet, Ros and lemonade concentrate in punch bowl and stir until well blended. Pour in champagne or sparkling Ros and serve at once. Garnish with berries or mint. Makes 1 gallon.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pecans
and coconut together in bowl.
Crush vanilla wafers in a blender and add to coconut and pecans;
mix well.
Cream the margarine
and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the margarine and sugar, beating well. Fold the dry ingredients into the egg mixture and
add 1/2 cup milk.
Pour the cake batter into a
well-greased
tube
pan. Bake
for
1 hour. Remove from pan when cool.
Slice
and
top with Cool Whip or ice cream (vanilla).

title: lemon pepper green beans
directions: Cook and drain beans; set aside.
Saute almonds in butter. Add lemon pepper.
Add beans.
Cook in microwave an additional 10 minutes on High.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in casserole.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with dried onion rings.

title: sweet potato squares
directions: Mix until crumbly and sprinkle over sweet potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve warm with dollop of whipped or sour cream.
Garnish with nutmeg.

title: orange beets
directions: Stir the cornstarch into 1/2 cup water.
Mix juice, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch, stirring until clear and thick.
Add the butter; stir well, then add the beets, stirring to coat well.

title: fluffy 2-step cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate for 3 hours. Top with cherry pie filling just before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas yams
directions: Layer yams in pan; add juice and oleo on top of yams.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: anybody's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and eggs; add Bisquick mix, nuts and coconut.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes (yields 40).

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Beat together in bowl, sugar, vanilla, margarine and eggs. Then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Good with milk!

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot
water
and
let
gel.
Mix instant pudding as directed.
After Jell-O
is set, put pudding on top and cover with Cool Whip.
Use
a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in boiling water, add cold water, cottage cheese and pineapple.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and chill until firm. Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water. Add cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Stir in oranges.
Pour mixture over first layer and chill until firm. Dissolve cherry gelatin in boiling water.
Add sour cream and pie filling and pour over second layer.
Chill until firm.
Spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: princely pork chops
directions: Pepper and flour chops.
Brown in oil. Drain off excess oil. Top each chop with a slice of onion, then a slice of lemon.
Mix water, sugar, catsup and liquid smoke.
Pour over chops.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare the pie crust.
In large bowl combine corn syrup, sugar, eggs, butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour filling into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with pecan halves.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set.
(Can also add 1/2 to 1 cup crushed pecans to mixture.)

title: chantilly cream squares
directions: Combine milk, cream, sugar, salt and syrup in sauce pan. Cook over low heat stirring constantly until 238 degrees on a candy thermometer or soft ball stage.
When cool add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and pour in shallow greased 11 x 7 pan.
When cool cut in squares and wrap.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Parboil ribs; save broth for sauce.
Cover ribs with Kraft mixture and cook in 350° oven until done.

title: minute muffins
directions: Put in a large bowl; mix all ingredients.
Blend until smooth. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: winnie-the-pooh cereal
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add honey, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Store in airtight container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese and butter soft, add onion.
Chill slightly to make it easy to form a ball.
After formed into a ball, roll in beef. Serve with crackers.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until softened.
Add eggs, 1 cup sugar, salt and almond extract.
Beat until smooth and thick.
Pour into spring pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set. Remove from oven and cool in pan on cake rack 20 minutes (top will crack).
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Pour over cooled cake.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes.
Cool and then chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip gradually until it is all mixed in thoroughly.
May be served immediately or chilled and served.

title: cheese spread for crackers
directions: If pineapple not drained well, will make it soft like a spread instead of a ball.

title: carrots of the ritz
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until almost done.
Drain and save liquid.
Coarsely mash carrots, add crushed crackers, onion, butter and 2/3 cup reserved liquid.
Mix well, place in small buttered baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dewberry cobbler
directions: Heat berries and 3/4 cup of sugar together.
Mix flour, 1 cup of sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Put melted butter in a large baking pan.
Add batter, then add berries without mixing or stirring.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush over hot biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve hot. Makes 10 to 12.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Heat broken almond bark at 200° for 10 minutes.
When soft, stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper; cool at room temperature until hard, about 1 hour.
Yields about 5 dozen.
Absolutely delicious.

title: corn
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot and cover. Pop over med. heat. Shake well. Make sure it does not burn.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook egg noodles following package directions.
While noodles cook, chop celery, onions, bell peppers and parsley.
Melt butter and put onions in for 10 minutes; add flour to butter and cook 10 minutes.
Add crawfish and simmer 20 minutes.
Add half and half, cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Let cheese melt.
Put noodles in pan, then pour sauce/crawfish on top. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine all in double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Cool and place in pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Take the beans, wash and run through hot water until beans are white again.
Put on the fire with the water.
Take the ham hocks and boil slowly, approximately 3 hours, in covered pot.
Braise the onion in a little butter and when light brown, put in bean soup.
Season with salt and pepper, then serve. Do not add salt until ready to serve.
Serves 8 persons.

title: onions with sage
directions: Peel the onions and leave them whole.
Heat the butter in a saucepan and brown the onions gently, stirring often.
Blend in flour and cook for 1 minute, then add heated chicken stock and stir until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then the chopped sage.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When the onions are soft all the way through, stir in the cream and parsley and serve.

title: cherry pink sponge
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cooked rice, salt, sugar and flavorings.
Chill until partially thickened.
Then add Cool Whip.
Let chill at least 2 hours.

title: mayonnaise biscuits or muffins
directions: Stir ingredients together until smooth. Drop from spoon into 6 greased muffin tins or cast-iron skillet. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown. You can also roll these out and cut with a biscuit cutter.

title: polenta
directions: Stir cornmeal in cold water.
Cook, stirring for 40 minutes until thick.
Add 1 tablespoon butter when done.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy apple strudel
directions: Combine flour, powder and salt. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Add milk. Stir until blended.
Knead gently 12 times. Roll dough (about 1/4-inch thick) into a rectangle. Brush with melted margarine.

title: shrimp
directions: Saute all vegetables in steak sauce, picante sauce and butter. Add crab meat and simmer quite awhile. Add shrimp. Enjoy.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in the bottom of casserole dish.
Bring soup and broth to a slow boil.
Pour over chicken. Salt and pepper chicken and broth mixture to taste.
In bowl, mix flour, milk and butter; pour over chicken and broth.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: barbecued chicken with honey-mustard glaze
directions: In a large screw-top jar, combine all ingredients, except chicken and glaze.
Cover and shake vigorously to blend.
In shallow dish, pour tomato sauce mixture over chicken.
Cover and marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill chicken over medium flame for 45 to 50 minutes, brushing with marinade and turning frequently.
Just before serving, brush with Honey-Mustard Glaze.

title: perfect caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Cook 2 minutes; add 1/4 cup milk.
Let come to a boil.
Cool and add powdered sugar.

title: applesauce granola cookies(sugarless)
directions: *Combine equal amounts of any combination:
rolled oats, nuts, coconut, finely chopped dried fruit or seeds.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Prepare mix as directed on back of box (can use 2 whole eggs instead of 3 whites if you want to).
Add coconut flavoring and frozen coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

Punch holes all over top of cake with toothpick or small straw while still warm. Heat the following mixture and pour over hot cake: evaporated milk, confectioners sugar and enough water to make mixture equal 2 cups.
Ice cooled cake with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with frozen coconut and store in refrigerator.
Real good and moist.

title: apple crisp
directions: Stir ingredients together and arrange in a 12 x 20-inch greased pan.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw broccoli.
Coat a 13 x 9 x 2 pan with cooking spray.
Stir first three ingredients together and then add others, combining all items in a bowl.
Place in baking dish and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
(Store leftovers in refrigerator.)
Yield: 15 servings.

title: "yummy smell"
directions: Bring to a boil in saucepan. Turn down to a simmer. Enjoy.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain off fat juice.
Mix other items and let simmer
on low heat.
Check often.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters; roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Spray muffin tin with Pam and put 4 quarters in each tin.
Combine butter, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over muffins (make pretty wet).
Bake 18 minutes at 350°.
Invert finished muffins on foil and pour syrup out of tin over top.

title: goop - silly putty
directions: Pour the glue into the starch and food coloring.
Mix well. This is a very long process; keep at it until mixture becomes spongy.
Knead the way you would bread dough.
Always add more starch, not more glue.
Good luck!

title: seafood spread
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
Makes 1 cup.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups water with the next 9 ingredients.
Add roast.
Cover and refrigerate 36 to 72 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove meat, wipe dry with paper towels. Strain marinade; reserve.
In Dutch oven, brown meat on all sides in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chopped vegetables.
Cover and cook slowly 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat; keep warm. Reserve 2 cups of liquid; add gingersnaps and 2/3 cup water.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Serve meat and sauce with hot buttered noodles.
Serves 8 to 10.
Well worth the effort!

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Put in baking dish.
For topping, mix 1/4 cup butter and corn flakes; sprinkle over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Take a fork and punch holes all in the cake.

title: rice and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients and place in large well-greased casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir once midway.

title: pineapple apricot salad
directions: Mix the pineapple and jello in the cup of hot water and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend in cream cheese. Refrigerate until partially set.
Fold in Cool Whip, celery and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips.
Pat dry.
Deep fry on high for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy. Drain. Combine hot sauce and butter.
Toss wings in sauce to coat completely.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini; drain and rinse in cold water.
Add carrots, broccoli and cauliflower.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Bring out, add cheese and the ranch dressing.
Mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Remove from heat and add salt, pepper and butter.
Add cracker crumbs, half grated cheese, milk and egg. Blend well.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
It is good made with Cheddar cheese, but coon cheese is delicious.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly. Add sugar and corn syrup. Add butter, salt, vanilla and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 300° to 325° and bake an hour.

title: microwave italian chicken and rice
directions: In a large dish combine chicken, squash, red pepper and salad dressing.
Let it sit for 20 minutes to 4 hours.
Transfer mixture to a colander.
In the dish, combine rice, water, herbs and bouillon.
Place colander with chicken mixture into dish.
Cover and cook on 100% power (High) for 7 to 8 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender, stirring once.
Let stand for 2 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Blend by hand the sour cream and cottage cheese.
Stir in green pepper, onion, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Serve on lettuce; sprinkle with dill.
This is pretty when used to stuff tomatoes. Also good for a low calorie dip.

title: pickled herring(sledzie marynowane)
directions: Soak herring in cold water for at least 24 hours.
Change water every 8 hours or more often.
Save the milch from herring.
Skin, remove bones and cut each herring into 4 pieces.
Arrange onions in a bed on a deep platter.
Arrange herring on top of onions.
Boil vinegar and cool.
Rub milch through fine sieve.
Mix with vinegar and sugar and pour over the herring.
Serve with whole boiled potatoes.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with frosting recipe following.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and boil over low heat to soft ball stage.
Stir in rest of ingredients and immediately pour into a 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Let set and cut into squares.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and put on stove, stirring continuously, until it thickens, approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from stove and pour in the strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour all into a prepared 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill well, about 2 hours. Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients; beat two to three minutes at medium speed.
Pour into three eight-inch round, greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 25 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, with sauteed celery and onions.
Pour in casserole dish.
Spoon cheese on top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: apple tapioca
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a saucepan and let stand for 5 minutes.
Cook about 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir constantly. Bring to boil; add vanilla.
Put apples in a buttered baking dish (3-quart); sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until brown on top.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease or line 8 muffin cups.
In large bowl combine all ingredients; stir 50 - 75 strokes until dry mix is moistened.
Fill greased or lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake for 17 - 21 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean Cool 5 minutes, remove from pan.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.
Yield:
20 side dish servings.
Great side dish with ham.

title: dijon shrimp scampi
directions: In large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook and stir shrimp and garlic in margarine until just pink.
Blend in mustard, lemon juice and parsley; heat through.
Serve over rice if desired. Serves 4.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve orange and lemon Jell-O in boiling water.
Soften unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Combine all Jell-O gelatin and other ingredients.
Pour into a greased dish and chill.

title: chili pizzeria
directions: Crumble beef.
Add onion and brown.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until macaroni is done.

title: lemon jelly roll cake
directions: Beat
egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add 1/2 the sugar slowly,
beating constantly.
Beat egg yolks in another bowl until
thick
and
lemon
colored.
Add
remaining sugar gradually,
continuing
to
beat
until stiff enough to hold a soft peak.
Add grated lemon rind and juice.
Fold gently into egg white
mixture.
Combine flour and salt and fold quickly, but lightly, into egg mixture.
Line shallow 11 x 16-inch pan with waxed
paper.
Pour
batter and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15
minutes, being careful not to overbake it.
Turn into
a clean towel, well sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Remove paper
and
trim
crust.
Roll,
lifting
end of towel nearest you.
Wrap in towel and cool.
Unroll; spread with jam or
jelly. Very
good if spread with Jell-O lemon pudding and pie filling.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt together.
Continue to add all the dry ingredients.
Slowly stir in salad oil and vanilla.
Add the grated zucchini.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 20.

title: pork chop marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients; let your pork chops marinate all day. We use 1/2 to 1-inch thick pork chops.
We also grill them outside.
This marinade is the best we have every found.
We have even tried it on ribs we do on the grill.

title: tijuana pie
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain, then add enchilada sauce.
Wipe crock-pot with oil, then layer tortilla, layer of meat, tortilla, corn, chili beans, tortilla, olives and cheese. Repeat layers, top with sauce and cheese.
Cook 8 hours on low.

title: holiday strata
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spray with Pam.
Arrange bread in overlapping rows.
Sprinkle with ham, cheese, peppers and onions.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add milk (use 2 3/4 cups if ham had water added).
Add seasonings.
Pour over bread and ham mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until knife is clean.
Remove from oven.
Let set about 10 minutes before serving.

title: lithuanian salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake well.

title: apple slices for decorations
directions: Cut off top and bottom of apples and slice in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Dip in lemon juice and place on paper towel.
Cook 30 seconds on High in microwave.
Remove and place on cookie sheet. Bake in regular oven at 200° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning once or twice.
Dry on wire rack 1 to 2 days.
Use in making wreaths, decorating baskets, etc.

title: grandmother's chicken casserole
directions: Cook, skin and debone chicken.
Chop onions and bell peppers. Dice up pimentos.
Cook egg noodles.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Put in baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put one cup of rice in round saucepan. Add water.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour can of French onion soup over chicken.
Last, spread mushroom soup on top of chicken.
Cook for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, onions and bell pepper.
Add eggs and cheese.
Mix well and stir in milk and sugar. Add bread crumbs; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered casserole dish and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Soak tortilla in boiling chicken broth for a few minutes; place in bottom of a 3-quart casserole.
Top with chicken pieces. Saute green pepper and onion in oil just until tender and layer over chicken.
Cover with cheese; sprinkle with chili powder, garlic powder and salt.
Spoon soups over casserole and top with tomatoes and chilies.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen and baked thawed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple slices
directions: Pour on the pie.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, parsley, salt, pepper, sugar and lemon juice in a large container with cover.
Add garlic and mushrooms. Marinate several hours or days in refrigerator.
Remove garlic and serve.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Add potatoes, sugar, vanilla and salt to melted margarine in a large skillet.
Cover, cook over medium heat for abut 45 minutes or until done.
You may have to add a little water, if needed.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs.
Mix baking powder and baking soda with flour.
Add flour mixture and milk into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Spray foil with Pam.
Line crackers up in pan.
In saucepan, melt butter; add brown sugar and bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes lowering temperature as you go. Pour this over crackers and bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chips on top.
Smooth over with back of spoon; must cover all crackers.
Add nuts if wanted.
Cool and cut.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Mix egg, clam chunks (drained), butter, garlic and bread crumbs.
Stuff mushrooms. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: In
3-quart
oblong
baking dish, place chicken and top with cheese.
Stir
soup
and
milk
together and spread over chicken and
cheese.
Top with tomato.
Combine margarine and stuffing mix together, then sprinkle over tomato slices.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: italian sausage soup with tortellini
directions: Remove casing from sausage if in casing. In 5-quart Dutch oven, brown sausage. Remove and drain, reserving its drippings. Saute garlic and onions in drippings until tender, but not brown. Add broth, water, wine, tomatoes, carrots, basil, oregano, tomato paste and sausage; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: jumbo shells with cheese filling
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package, cooking 9 minutes; drain. Rinse with cold water; drain and arrange in single layer to fill.

Meanwhile, mix together cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Fill cooked shells with cheese mixture. Cover bottom of roasting pan with some of the sauce. Arrange filled shells in single layer in the pan. Pour remaining sauce over the shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, oil and 1/2 cup water.
Beat 2 minutes. Add eggs, cherries and remaining water.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake in 2 or 3 (9-inch) greased and lined cake pans in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost layers with uncooked cherry chocolate icing (recipe follows).

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and Italian sausage.
Drain off oil.
Place on doubled paper towels to get out oil.
Slice sausage into desired shape.
Brown onion, garlic and bell peppers in 2 tablespoons of olive oil.
After obtaining desired texture, add spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and cilantro.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add beef and sausage and simmer 30 minutes.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of big bowl; add a layer of celery, peppers, onions and peas.
Do not toss; spread Miracle Whip over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Toss and add bacon bits if desired.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and
eggs.
Beat
at
medium speed 3 minutes; add vanilla.
Combine
dry ingredients;
add to above mixture.
Fold in chopped apples and pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake is done.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Mix in flour and salt. Chill for 2 hours; make into 24 small balls (walnut size).
Press into tiny muffin tins.

title: frozen cocktail salad
directions: Drain cocktail.
Soften cream cheese and blend with mayonnaise and lemon peel.
Stir in cocktail and marshmallows. Whip cream with powdered sugar until stiff.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into loaf pan lined with waxed paper.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold and slice.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Saute garlic in butter; let cool.
Add softened cheese and mix well (spreading consistency).
Spread this mixture on crust.
Add a small amount of cheese.
Add vegetables, shrimp and remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, pudding and spice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust.
Chill.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, meal, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in cheese, corn, chilies, milk and oil.
Beat eggs until yolks and whites are combined.
Add to cornmeal mixture. Stir until blended.
Turn into 9-inch square oiled pan.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown, about 35 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli. Cook rice as directed on package. Saute onion and celery in a little oil. Stir in broccoli and rice. Add soup and milk. Stir in Cheez Whiz and mix well. Bake in 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: eleanor's hot chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken and celery and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
When well blended, stir in chicken and celery thoroughly.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole and cover.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve over hot chow mein noodles or serve noodles on the side.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix next 3 ingredients together. Sprinkle crumble mixture over the top of the apple mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, egg yolks and milk; cook over medium heat until comes to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Layer with wafers and bananas.
Top with meringue.

title: quick-rise bread
directions: Stir together the yeast, dry milk, salt and 3 cups flour until well blended.
Add the warm water, honey, egg and oil.
Mix at medium speed for 3 minutes with an electric mixer.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender, pour over greens, toss.
Add anchovies and croutons.

title: willard long's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and eggs.
Add hot water, soda, flour and flavoring.
Beat well, then add nutmeats, chips and oatmeal.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute pepper and onion in oil until tender.
In a bowl, combine flour, salt, sugar, mustard, paprika and pepper.
Stir in the milk until smooth and add to skillet. Bring to a boil; cook and stir about 2 minutes until thick.
Stir in thawed corn and slightly beaten egg.
Pour into a quart baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Toss cornflakes and butter together and sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until center is partially set.

title: cookie bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
When well blended, fold in nuts. Bake in a greased and floured large tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Cook sugar and water until sugar melts; set off and let cool. Add pineapple juice, lemon juice, bananas (blended in blender) and orange juice.
Mix and freeze until ready to use.
Add 3 liters Sprite.

title: baked salmon in microwave
directions: Season to taste.
Cover with lite Italian dressing and light butter.
Bake 5 minutes in microwave.
Great!

title: club soda pancakes(oooh, so light!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook pancakes in the regular way.
Keep pan cakes hot in a serving dish until served.
This batter can not be saved like regular mix due to the club soda. Pancakes left over can be refrigerated or frozen.
Delicious!

title: chocolate snappers
directions: In a small bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, combine shortening, sugars and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Mix in corn syrup and melted chocolate.
Beat in flour mixture.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Allow to cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: crispy corn dogs
directions: Pat hot dogs dry with paper towels.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and cornmeal. Cut in shortening thoroughly.
Stir in egg and milk.
Dip hot dogs in batter, allowing excess batter to drip into bowl.
Fry in hot oil in fryer until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Insert wooden skewer in end of each corn dog.

title: strawberry-rice salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool; add rice, marshmallows and pineapple.
When mixture begins to gel, add Cool Whip and chill.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Scald 1
quart milk.
Mix sugar and Crisco together and add to milk; cool.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup of warm
water.
Add enough flour (about 7 cups) to make a dough with the
consistency
of cake dough.
Let rise 1 hour. Mix baking powder
and
salt and sprinkle over bread mixture. Dissolve soda in	1/4
cup water and pour over bread mixture. Stir in
well. Add
about	3
cups
of
flour to make biscuit dough.
Refrigerate for
minutes
before making biscuits. Dough may be kept in sealed container in refrigerator and used as needed.
Cook biscuits at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
They do not need to rise before baking.

title: vegetable layered salad
directions: Chop lettuce into bite size and spread into a 9 x 12-inch glass bowl.
Spread celery over lettuce, then onion, then pepper and last, peas.
Cover and seal edges with mayonnaise.
Crumble bacon bits and sugar over top.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top. Cover and seal with Saran Wrap for 24 hours in refrigerator. Serves 10.

title: scrapple
directions: In small bowl, blend together cornmeal and 1 cup water.
In large saucepan, combine pork sausage, sage, salt, parsley and chicken broth.
Gradually stir in 2 cups of water, being careful to separate sausage into fine pieces.
Bring to boiling.
Slowly add cornmeal to boiling mixture, stirring constantly with whisk. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Turn into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Cool; refrigerate, covered.

title: carrot and potato casserole(huisput)
directions: Cook carrots and potatoes until tender.
Drain, saving a little of the liquid.
Mash together with a little of the cooking liquid.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Continue to mash until mashed potato consistency.
Top with 8 pieces of American cheese and bake at 400° for 10 minutes or slightly browned on top. Serves 6.

title: open quesadilla
directions: Get a tortilla and some Cheddar cheese.
Grate the cheese.
Put it on the tortilla.
Cook it in the oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until melted and eat up.

title: easy leek soup for two
directions: Cut leek into 1-inch sections and cut each section lengthwise so that you can wash away all sand.
Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan; cover and bring to a boil.
Uncover; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Puree in blender until creamy.
Makes 2 servings.

title: crispy salsa potato skins
directions: Pierce potatoes with fork.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.
Cool!
Cut potato in half crosswise, then cut into half again.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Place potato shells, skin side down, on a foiled lined broiler pan.
Brush shells inside out with melted butter.
Bake skins until crisp and browned, about 12 minutes.
Preheat broiler; mix tomatoes, chilies and green onions in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheese. Broil until cheeses are bubbly.
Place potato skins on a serving platter.
Divide salsa evenly among skins.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: creamy chicken salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Miracle Whip. Add salt and onion powder; stir. Add chicken, celery and chopped onion. Use as a sandwich spread or serve on crackers.

title: "healthy" eggplant parmesan
directions: Wash and peel eggplant.
Slice into 1/2-inch rounds.
Boil for 10 minutes in 3 to 4 quarts of salted water.
Drain and layer eggplant in baking dish with sauce.
Top with cheeses.
Add mushrooms and oregano, if you like.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy lime pie
directions: Combine milk, lime rind and juice in a large bowl. Fold in whipped topping and food coloring, blending well. Spoon into crust and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: pickled squash
directions: Sprinkle salt on vegetables.
Cover with water and let stand for 2 hours; drain.
Heat sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, prepared mustard and turmeric to a boil.
Pour vegetables in and bring to boil second time.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes approximately 5 pints.

title: celery fish fillets
directions: Mix soup, milk and water.
Put fillets in baking pan and pour half of soup mixture on top, then slice cucumber (thinly); put on top of fish.
Pour rest of soup mixture on top of cucumbers and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Top with 2 cups of assorted fruit of choice.

title: hellmann's chocolate cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Blend until mixture is smooth.
Pour into lined cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Let cake cool and frost.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Use with any vegetables or crackers.

title: carp curry with coriander and tomato
directions: This carp curry, which freezes well, can also be made with catfish, bass, trout, perch, etc.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut in quarters 1/2 bushel tomatoes.
Cook and put through sieve.
Grind together onions, celery, hot peppers and garlic. Add to tomato juice along with oil, salt, sugar, parsley, Italian seasoning and tomato paste.
Cook down for one hour.
Pour into quart jars and seal.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and mix in remaining ingredients. Pour in freezer bowl and place in freezer.
Stir several times while freezing to mix.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.
Place unused salad back into freezer.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: cranberry and yam bake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, oatmeal and cinnamon together; cut in margarine until it looks like coarse crumbs.
Toss yams and cranberries with this mixture.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.
If desired, you can drizzle with small amount of honey before adding marshmallows. You can make it pretty.

title: crab canapes
directions: Combine ingredients (except English muffins).
Spread about 2 teaspoons on cut side of English muffin half.
Cut each into 4 piece triangles.
Place on baking sheets; freeze at least 30 minutes (may be frozen up to 2 months).

title: fresh berries with orange cream
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Cut in half or leave whole.
Combine them with 1 tablespoon of sugar in a small bowl.

title: russian salad dressing
directions: Mix well in blender or mixer.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover celery with water.
Boil 12 minutes, add potato and carrot and boil 15 more minutes.
Add milk and butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crackers.
Do not drain water, vitamins and minerals are in the water.
A favorite during the Great Depression 1929-36.
I make it often.

title: steak or what?
directions: Pat ground beef evenly into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Spread the boiled potatoes, onion and peas evenly over it.
Salt and pepper to taste. Mix cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups and spread evenly on top. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over high heat.
Add onions; cook and stir until softened and slightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Stir in wine; simmer about 10 more minutes.
Combine onions, broth, thyme, salt and worcestershire in crockpot.
Cover and cook on low for 4-5 hours.
(I cook mine all night/day.) Ladle soup into individual bowls; top with toasted bread and cheese.
Heat under broiler to melt cheese.
Garnish with thyme.

title: hearty beef-n-vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange frozen potatoes in bottom and up sides of 8 x 12-inch baking dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: refreshing drink
directions: Pour into 2-quart pitcher.
Adds color to table setting and is refreshing to drink.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt on low heat butterscotch chips; stir constantly.
When melted, add peanut butter.
Take off heat.
When all mixed up, add peanuts, marshmallows and Chinese noodles.
Mix all together. Spoon out onto wax paper until firm.

title: patsy salad
directions: Chop cabbage (bite-size); chop pecans coarsely.
Chop apples into small pieces.
Mix up in bowl; add cherries.
In small bowl, mix together all of the other ingredients; pour the chopped mixture.
Mix well.
Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Mix thoroughly.
Put the vinegar and Worcestershire sauce in a blender.
Gradually add dry ingredients while blender is going.
Blend to velvety smoothness. Makes 8 to 9 ounces.

title: spring garden dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well and put into small bowl.
Serve with fresh vegetables and crackers.

title: squash casserole i
directions: Mix squash, salt, pepper, onions, sour cream and soup.
Mix melted margarine with the stuffing mix.
Line casserole with about 1/2 of the stuffing; add squash to top of stuffing and put remaining stuffing mix on top.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix sugar, flour and baking soda.
Stir in egg whites, oil, bananas, buttermilk, raisins and apricots.
Stir only to combine. Do not overbeat.
Fill 24 paper lined muffin tins.
Sprinkle oat bran on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: stuffed meat steak
directions: If steak is not tenderized, beat the steak up well with a meat tenderizer until it is tender.
Cut steak up into little 3-inch strips.
Fry steak just until it is browned on both sides.
Do not roll in flour.
Take off stove, drain and cool.

title: corn dogs
directions: Take 8 to 10 frankfurters and dip into batter.
Then put them into hot oil until golden brown.
Oil should be 375°.

title: oven fried fish a la orange
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Combine crumbs and 1 teaspoon salt.
Dip fish in egg mixture, then in crumb mixture.
Place skin side down in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine; stir in lemon juice.
Drizzle over fish. Bake in 500° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: **fine peach pudding
directions: Beat eggs until thick and foamy.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to eggs.
Beat, beat and beat.
Add milk and beat some more.
Pour mixture over peaches (or other fruit) in casserole or any baking dish.
Bake at 325° until it sets (about one hour).

title: swiss chard mornay
directions: Wash and drain Swiss
chard.
Cut
off	stalks	and cut into one inch pieces.
Coarsely	chop
leaves.
Bring one inch of water to a boil in
a Dutch oven over high heat.	Add Swiss chard stalks and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer
covered 5
minutes.
Stir
in
chopped
leaves.
Cook covered 3 to 5 minutes;
drain well. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a 2 quart saucepan over medium heat.	Stir in flour and 1/2 teaspoon	salt. Gradually stir
in
milk
until
mixture
is smooth.
Cook, stirring
until
mixture
boils
and
thickens. Remove from heat. Stir in chard and cheeses, then turn into a 2 quart casserole sprayed with nonstick coating (or butter and flour casserole). Top with
bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and bake at
425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Butter a baking dish about 10-inches square.
Lay in it a layer of potatoes, onion, ham and cheese and season with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Continue this procedure until ingredients are used up.
Pour in milk so that it is just even with the top layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: julie's yummy salsa
directions: Mix and chill. Serve with Doritos or Tostitos.

title: graham cracker delectables
directions: Melt margarine or butter and brown sugar together; stir well. Add chopped pecans.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool.
Cut in 1 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch pieces (1/2 graham cracker square).

title: fourth of july bean casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon, beef and onion.
Drain.
Place in 2 1/2-quart greased baking dish with all beans.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to casserole dish.
Mix well.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on box.
Let Jell-O cool a little. Punch holes in cake with a wooden spoon.
Pour Jell-O over cake and put in refrigerator until Jell-O gels.
May be served with Cool Whip.
This is a good summer dish!

title: walter's pancakes
directions: Melt shortening; add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cook on hot griddle.
Serve hot with maple syrup.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Take one roll of cookie mix and slice it.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and press together.
Pour filling over dough. Slice other roll of dough and lay on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pie crusts
directions: Let margarine and cheese set at room temperature.
Put in other ingredients.
Make dough.
Refrigerate to cool.
Roll out. Makes 4 pie crusts.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Boil hen until tender.
Remove from bone and chip into small pieces.
Cook noodles in broth.
Prepare sauce by melting margarine and adding chopped peppers, onions and pimento.
Cook until soft; then add chopped mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, chicken and peas.
Simmer a few minutes and add to drained noodles.

title: "eat one-freeze one" italian casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown beef and drain, then add spaghetti sauce.
In another bowl, blend the Egg Beaters, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
Spray two 9-inch square casseroles with Pam cooking spray.
Pour a little of the spaghetti-meat mixture on the bottom of each dish, then spread 1/2 of the Ricotta cheese mix over this layer.
Next, place 1/2 of the noodles over the cheese layer.
Repeat layers again.
Top with the Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over 4 to 6 pieces of chicken. Marinate 2 hours but better overnight.
Turn chicken occasionally. Keep refrigerated.
Cook chicken on barbecue grill until done.

title: hamburger noodle bake(serves 12)
directions: In skillet cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned; add onions until tender.
Drain off fat.
Combine meat and onion with noodles, cheese soup, 1 cup water, green pepper, chili sauce, pimento, salt and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle atop. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until hot.
Trim with green pepper rings if desired.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Combine with all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Roll in nuts and chill.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Melt cream cheese with tomato soup in a double boiler until well blended.
Mix reserved shrimp liquid with Knox gelatine. Add to soup and cheese mixture. Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm. Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 16 balls.
In skillet, brown meatballs in small amount of oil.
Drain off fat.
Blend soup and water to meat balls in pan. Cook over low heat 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and chopped nuts and spread in bottom of oblong pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix margarine with sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Add plain flour and milk alternately.
Then flavoring.
Put in greased and slightly floured tube pan.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: macaroon bar
